full_description:

Tara's owner's children relinquished her when their mother's advanced dementia made her no longer able to care for Tara. She is a beautiful tuxedo kitty who was shy at first, certainly confused by the sudden change in her surroundings. She has warmed up quickly to become a calm, affectionate cat initiating interaction and seeking pets and attention. Tara loves to be petted and talked to. In her previous home, she lived happily with dogs, and she gets along with other cats. Since she can be timid at first, Tara may do best with older, respectful children. She is a sweet, gentle cat. You'll love her.

Pre-adoption Application

name: Puma
description: Puma is a friendly five-month-old kitten who needs a home.  Once you earn his trust, it will not take long...
full_description:
Puma is a friendly five-month-old kitten who needs a home. Once you earn his trust, it will not take long for him to show how warm, friendly, and playful he is. We have not observed him with dogs or kids, but we believe he'll do well with kids who know how to treat cats respectfully. Kittens this young need at least one other four-legged pal in their homes, and this little guy's no exception. He can be adopted with his mother Nefertiti (posted separately, and barely older than a kitten herself) or into a home that already have a cat or cat-friendly dog. Puma is a little bundle of playfulness who will bring an abundance of love and laughter to any home.

He has been:
- neutered
- vaccinated a age-appropriate
- tested negative for FeLV and FIV
- treated for worms and fleas

His adopter will receive his medical records. There is a simple adoption process and an adoption fee so we can continue to help cats in need. A small discount will apply if he and his mother are adopted together. They're being fostered in Cambridge.

Cats can live up to 20 years, so give careful thought to the changes that are likely to occur in your life during that time. If you can and will commit to him and provide a safe, loving home for life, then respond to RoyCBarrows@gmail.com. Please include your phone number for a faster response and say a little about yourself and the home you would provide for him as we try to match people with the right cats.

full_description:
MEET LONNIE

LONNIE was found as a stray in West Virginia and brought to the pound. We were asked to bring Lonnie north by our partner rescuer to make sure he never ever ended up in the pound again. Lonnie is so sweet. A gentle companion ready for adventures. He is dog friendly but would prefer calmer dogs in the home. We can cat test if needed.

From Lonnie’s foster:

Lonnie is doing great- it’s hard not to fall in love with him!
He’s extremely sweet and easy going. He’s great on the leash, never pulls, and never barks. He’s been picking up going Potty outside as he’s treat motivated but more than anything, he loves being praised and called a good boy!
He LOVES to be around people and will happily soak up all the attention you give him. He’s definitely got some qualities of a little Velcro dog.



*TO APPLY GO TO www.LuckyDogRefuge.com
(Petfinder messages will not be seen.)




NOTE: We do not know the exact breeds of our dogs; any mention of breeds are best guesses and not guaranteed.
No dog is going to be perfectly housebroken when they go to a new home. They are accustomed to the routine of the shelter and will need to learn the new routine in their new environment. They will need your patience as they might have some accidents in the home while they get adjusted.

YOU CAN ALSO APPLY VIA THE DIRECT LINK BELOW.

https://www.luckydogrefuge.com/adoption-application.html

full_description: Lydia is a friendly and affectionate adult dog, about 1 year old, who loves making new friends. She is an intelligent dog who responds well to training, and with the right family, she will be a very well-behaved companion. She has a friendly personality and would likely be a good playmate for a fellow canine. If you're looking for a loyal and loving companion, Lydia is the perfect addition to your family.  Lydia can't wait to meet you and jump into your loving arms.

description: Meet the 3 Musketeers. Lemon, Cappuccino and Raspberry. These stunning 12 week old kittens were born at our Cattail Farm...
full_description:
Meet the 3 Musketeers. Lemon, Cappuccino and Raspberry. These stunning 12 week old kittens were born at our Cattail Farm shelter location and are the remaining 3 kittens from a litter of 5 born to their extraordinary mother, Lilou.
Lemon is a male, Flame Point Siamese
Cappuccino is a male, with a rich coat of buff colored fur, like his mom
Raspberry, is a female and a classic orange tabby

We are offering these kittens as a package deal believing no one should have to choose and leave one behind! They are deeply bonded. They are snuggle bugs and love to play but like all kittens, crash hard, together in a kitten pile, when it's time to rest.

A home with "older" children would be wonderful for them. Given the hope that they will be adopted together, being the only furry family members might be best for them. Lemon, Cappuccino and Raspberry are currently living on Drake's Island with their Foster Family and adoption visits will take place in the foster's home.

If you would like to know more about these incredible family, please take a moment to complete our online application found at:
https://www.safehavenhumanesociety.org/adoption-form/

All 3 kittens require one more vet visit for their final Distemper Booster, Rabies Vaccination and Microchipping. That is about 4 weeks out. But we would welcome visits before that.

full_description:

When we were contacted about Dottie’s situation, we knew we had to try. This sweet 7 year old girl has spent the last couple of years in a small, confined space, unable to safely roam the home due to the resident dogs. Her family recognizes that this is no life for her. They took her in when their son could no longer care for her and have tried to make it work over the last few years, but they are now desperate to find her a loving home where she can have the comfort and care she deserves.

Dottie is a diabetic cat, and sadly, so many cats like her are overlooked because of the fear surrounding medical management. But the truth is, feline diabetes can be manageable! With a proper routine, insulin, and diet control, diabetic cats can live happy and fulfilling lives. The commitment is real, but so is the reward—you’re giving a cat like Dottie a second chance at happiness.

? ???? ?????????? ??? ???? ????? ????, ??? ??? ?? ?????????? ?????????.

She is extremely sweet, with the cutest little trot when she walks. Despite her age, she’s still playful and adores her catnip toys. One of her funniest little quirks is that she loves to lay down while she eats or drinks.

????? ???, ??? ??????? ?? ???? ?? ?????????, ??? ??????? ? ????, ??? ?????? ?? ?????????.

Her family has even considered euthanasia, not because they want to let her go, but because they don’t want her to continue living without the space, care, and comfort she deserves. That’s why they reached out to us—to try everything before making that heartbreaking decision. We don’t want to see her life cut short when all she needs is someone willing to give her the love and care she deserves.

description: Bentley is ready to find a new family and home to begin a better life then what he has had...
full_description: Bentley is ready to find a new family and home to begin a better life then what he has had in the past. Originally he was surrendered to a person who gave him away when they decided they didn't want him any more. Then he was given away again to someone who didn't treat him very well.  He was then left outside, scared and not understanding why he was abandoned. Our rescue was called and we took Bentley so he could decompress and we could find him a better life. This fellow is about 6 years old and would love to bond with people who will make him a part of their family and treat him well. He is very deserving of an owner who is understanding and looking for a companion or friend for another dog.  He currently is a little timid probably due to everything he has been through.  Bentley would love to become part of a new family this spring. Could you give him a chance and meet him?

full_description: Meet Leo, a dog whose heart is as big as his personality. His sweet, friendly nature makes him the perfect companion for anyone seeking a loyal friend. full_description: Meet Pearl, a cat who is as precious as her namesake. She has a friendly demeanor that brightens up any room she enters. Yet, Pearl also values her independence, content to explore her surroundings or find a quiet corner to nap in. Despite her lively nature, Pearl is a quiet companion, making her the perfect fit for those seeking a pet that won't disturb their peace. Pearl's blend of friendliness, playfulness, and independence makes her a delightful presence. She has so much love and joy to share, and she's waiting for the perfect family to share it with. Bring Pearl home and experience the unique charm she adds to everyday life.

name: Jett
description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Hatch Date: 2024

Jett is a very handsome 10-month-old...
full_description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Hatch Date: 2024

Jett is a very handsome 10-month-old Black-capped Conure.
He has been disease tested and DNA tested Male.

We are still working with him on trusting and becoming hand-tame, but he has the potential to become an amazing companion.
Looking for the right person or family with older children and patience.
Each day he seems more and more comfortable with the presence of hands.
We have discovered that some of his favorite snacks are Cashews, Apples, Grape Nuts, and Birdy Bistro.

Jett enjoys taking daily baths in his water bowl, as staying handsome and bright is one of his top priorities! ;)
Jett is not a very vocal Conure, but I'm sure in time that will change, as he is still very young and learning every day.
Right now, he has two cockatiels keeping him company and he will sometimes screech to shut them up.
It's quite funny! Otherwise, he is very quiet and mainly keeps to himself playing with and shredding his toys.
He is interested in other birds and seems very intrigued...especially by the Cockatoo in his foster home.

Jett loves to snuggle up under his rope toy before bedtime and will sometimes allow scratches on his head while doing this,
which is why we feel in time he will learn to trust more and more.
We have only had Jett for a little over a week, so we are still getting to know him,
but from what we can tell, he will be a wonderful lifetime companion.
We will keep the updates coming.

Jett is being fostered in Hillsborough, NJ.
You must be within driving distance to make the required visits and to adopt.
We do not ship our birds.
For t he Love of Birds is a network of dedicated foster homes
throughout NJ and Eastern PA. As our adoptable birds live in volunteer homes, we only allow approved adopters to make the required visits. I
f interested in adopting Jett, please visit our website ftlob.rescuegroups.org Please read our adoption policies and fees and complete an adoption application.

Shona (Latino) is a Female, and Panna (Grey) is a male.They are a bonded pair of Cockatiels that have been together for 20 years.They are very shy and skittish of peopleWatching the happenings in the neighborhood through the large window seems to be their favorite activity.Their foster home is working on getting them to eat a healthier diet. They have already started to nibble on pellets.These two need a quiet environment where they can live out their retirement years :) Shona and Panna are being fostered in Leonardo, NJ

For the Love of Birds is a network of dedicated foster homes throughout NJ and Eastern PA.
We have no central location.
You must be within driving distance to make the required visits and to adopt.
We will NOT ship our birds.
As our adoptable birds are living in volunteer homes, or their family home,
we only allow approved applicants to meet our birds.
If you are interested in meeting Shona and Panna, please review our adoption policies
and complete an adoption application on our website ftlob.rescuegroups.org.

full_description:
Toby - Male DOB 4/24/2024 Domestic Short Hair - Brown/White Tabby

Toby is a shy boy and still taking some time to settle into our quiet room. He will take a little time to settle into his new surroundings and to gain his trust that he isn't going to be harmed. Once he does, he is a very sweet and loving boy. He loves to be petted and will roll over in delight as you pet him. He has a hardy appetite and loves his wet food. He's playful, and social around the other cats, and would need to go home with another friendly kitten, like his BFF Trinity, or home to another young calm, sweet cat. He would do best with no dogs, and no children.

Please apply via our easy online application at https://furrr.org/cat-adoption-process/All kitten(s) and cat(s) at FuRRR Feline Rescue are spayed/neutered, up to date on vaccinations for their age, combo tested for FIV/FeLV, microchipped and have a Health Certificate from a licensed NH veterinarian. Our application is available to be completed online at https://furrr.org/cat-adoption-process/ Applying DOES NOT guarantee approval. We hold meet and greets with approved applications only. (Kittens are available for adoption in pairs only unless they are going home to another kitten or young cat under 3) Our policy is strictly NO DECLAWING and INDOOR ONLY.

Meet Layla - A Sweet Soul Ready for Her Forever Home!

Layla is a loving girl looking for a fresh start in a safe, caring home. She's great with dogs and kids of all ages, but her compatibility with other cats is still unknown. Layla is an absolute sweetheart who is always purring and loves to chat with you. She has been through quite a lot, and now she deserves to find a loving family that will cherish her.

Layla was surrendered to GRASP when her caretaker realized she was pregnant. Unfortunately, Layla needed to undergo an emergency surgery following miscarriage.

Layla has a heart full of love, and after everything she's been through, she deserves to be pampered and cared for in a home where she can thrive. Let's help Layla find the happy ending she's been waiting for.

Apply to adopt Layla today!

full_description:
Please contact the Cat Team (catapplications@graspinc.org) for more information about this pet.
DOB 4/6/24

This beautiful young lady wants the world to know that "affectionate" is her middle name. She's hoping you have a last name to give her.

Dani adores a good play session - be it wand toys, ping pong balls or mouse toys, she's game. Agile and active, she would be thrilled to have a cat tree in her forever home, as well as a cozy bed when she decides to rest. Dani loves to be petted, snuggled, given belly rubs and having her striking coat brushed. She is content to settle on a human lap or curl up with them while they sleep.

Silly and social, Dani has lived with other kitties in the past and enjoys the companionship of another feline. She isn't afraid to take the lead in this relationship, but is also respectful of the older kitties she has lived with. She has not met a dog or very young children, though she is comfortable with children older than 5, as well as teenagers (she's a fantastic study buddy).

Apply to adopt this charismatic girl and bring her cuddles into your home and family!

This cat has been combo-tested for Feline Leukemia and FIV, received all age-appropriate vaccinations and is altered.

full_description:

In her foster home, she is working hard on her house-training, crate training, and leash walking. She could go to a home with kids 5+, cats, and other dogs.

Her foster says, "Daisy is such a social butterfly that we could not keep her downstairs with the other retirement pups. Nope. She wanted to be the life of the party on the play yard. name: Mylo-Soft 'n Cuddly
description:
Courtesy Post for another rescue group.

Meet MYLO! This handsome boy is a "purr monster"! Estimated to be around 11...
full_description:
Courtesy Post for another rescue group.

Meet MYLO! This handsome boy is a "purr monster"! Estimated to be around 11 mos old, this adorable guy is such a love bug. He just wants to melt in your arms. Mylo and 2 of his presumed litter mates came in to a No.Carolina shelter together. The caller stated that her neighbor moved out and left 3 cats there. She is an elderly lady that did her best but said they were too sweet to continue to live outdoors. Animal control went to set a trap and she came out across the yard holding all three of them. They were loved and cared for once upon a time, as Mylo is extremely loving and was in good health. Mylo is a sweet boy, who loves attention. He would make a great starter cat for anyone looking to add a sweet lap warmer to the family. He has a plush fur coat and likes to play and LOVES to cuddle even more; he purrs non-stop when he sees you and especially when held. While this bright-eyed boy is very curious, he settles down nicely to hang in his bed. He is up to date on vaccinations, and litter box trained. Given his young age, playful nature and compatibility with other cats, Mylo would love to be adopted into a home with another gentle feline. He also might be OK with a work-from-home human that will play and cuddle with him a lot. Are you willing to swish the fishing pole toy for this sweet, gentle boy? Posted 3/12/25

name: Cassie
description:

Posted 3/12/2025

Cassie is a sweet 8-month-old, 42-pound Boxer/Hound mix pup....
full_description:
Please read our Core Values prior to applying, www.furryfriendsnetwork.com/adopt/our-expectations.

Posted 3/12/2025

Cassie is a sweet 8-month-old, 42-pound Boxer/Hound mix pup. She is a happy, sweet and affectionate girl with a big smile. Yes! She smiles when she is happy and excited! Cassie shares her foster home with two small, elderly dogs, and a medium-size dog. Cassie has typical puppy energy and loves attention. She enjoys playing and running with her canine friends and enjoys a game of fetch. When she is not playing, she is following her humans around or chewing on a Nylabone. Cassie also tones it down in the evenings to snuggle with her humans.

Cassie gets along with everyone she has met so far in canine and human form. She is housebroken but must be taken out regularly to avoid accidents. As a puppy, she is still learning the world around her and can be spooked by loud noises such as buses and garbage trucks while on walks. She needs a bit of patience and positive reinforcement in those instances. Cassie tends to jump when she gets excited or wants to play. We are currently working with her on this as well all basic commands. She is food motivated and takes treats very gently. Cassie is crate trained and sleeps in her crate throughout the night with no issues. She whines a bit when she knows we are going away but that subsides.

An ideal home for Cassie would be with someone who is active and who will make time for walks, car rides, play, and training. She would even be a fantastic running partner! Obedience training will help her gain confidence and will go a long way in developing and earning her trust with her new family. Cassie is an eager learner who wants to impress and win over her humans. She loves playing with dogs so another dog would be a bonus but not a necessity. She was fine with cats in the shelter but is not currently living with them. Cassie is really is a sweet girl who deserves a family who will love her furrrrever!

Contact generalinfo@furryfriendsnetwork.com for questions or if issues are encountered with the adoption application or general adoption process.

Foster Homes are desperately needed in order to help more animals like this one. Please consider opening your heart and home to a homeless animal. To find out more about becoming a Foster Parent, see our website at www.furryfriendsnetwork.com. Look under VOLUNTEER tab.

full_description:
Please share this amazing boy with all your friends and help him find his forever home.
Mac is a smart boy with a loving, playful personality...and the softest belly i have ever had the honor pet. He'd really love a family of homebodies because he'd rather not be alone....ever. But if you have to leave him, he does have a Fort Knox strong crate to keep him safe.

Looking for a couch potato dog, well Mac is for you! He does love to sleep on the couch but also loves to play with the fosters dog. He listens well when he is off leash in the backyard. He also gets excited to go on the 2 mile walk with his foster mom and walks well on leash. He loves his foster mom and likes to follow her around. name: Pippy- Yorkie of Unusual Size
description: PIPPY, the Yorkie of Unusual Size, is a new local surrender and is an adorable 40 lb Yorkie mix of...
full_description:
PIPPY, the Yorkie of Unusual Size, is a new local surrender and is an adorable 40 lb Yorkie mix of some sort (with something bigger than a Yorkie, of course!) He's a super sweet dog who we are getting all vetted and scheduled for neuter (which will be included in his adoption fee at our vet even if he is adopted before that date). He's 4 years old, and was great with people, including the school-aged kids kids and cats in his previous home. He was also great with other dogs when he came across them while camping and on walks, but only did not get along with the dog in his home, so one had to go. It may have been the other dog, it's hard for us to know. We've only had him for a short time and are easing into interactions with other dogs just to be sure, but so far so good.

Adoption fee INCLUDES: all vetting to age (including deworming, flea & tick etc), spay/neuter and microchip (if the dog is under 6 months, alter and chip will occur after they're 6 months, covered in full at our clinic or reimbursed partially at a vet of your choosing). If the dog is older than 6 months and not yet altered, we will schedule ASAP (normally within 30 days) at our clinic . We also provide as an incentive a $60 rebate for completion of positive-based training classes. Adoption also includes lifetime support of the rescue.

Please fill out an APPLICATION here for consideration: www.tinyurl.com/appshdr (copy and paste link into browser window if link is not active in your browser).

We do most application processing virtually and dog meets will be individually by appointment with ONLY APPROVED APPLICANTS. We are not a shelter and are completely volunteer foster-based, so there is no central place to come see all of the dogs available.

IMPORTANT NOTES: ** Housetraining with rescues is sometimes a work in progress and even if a dog is 100% in a foster's home, it should be expected there will be an adjustment period as a dog adapts to a new environment. This is even more true if the dog has not by chance had their altering appointment at time of adoption. ** Also, we highly recommend some form of 2-week shutdown and decompression for dogs going to a new home for best results. --> Lastly, breed guesses in rescue are just that (GUESSES!!) 99.9% of the time. We do not do DNA testing and our breed guesses are based on appearance and sometimes other traits, but we know the dog breed guessing game is a fool's errand even for those with LOTS of experience.

PLEASE NOTE: If a dog is listed as Adoptable, he or she is still available at that time. Also, our adoption area is within a several hour radius of us in Rochester, NY (Canada within 3 hours IS allowed, except that young puppies need to be old enough to have gotten their rabies vaccination to cross the border - usually around 16 weeks)

name: Bobby
description:
Please read our Core Values prior to applying, www.furryfriendsnetwork.com/adopt/our-expectations.

Posted 3/12/2025

Bobby had a very rough life. He has made...
full_description:
Please read our Core Values prior to applying, www.furryfriendsnetwork.com/adopt/our-expectations.

Posted 3/12/2025

Bobby had a very rough life. He has made amazing progress since coming into rescue and continues to blossom every day.

Bobby is an amazing combination of scent and sight dog. We are not sure of his exact breed mix. He has the cutest spotted ears, webbed feet, always has his nose to the ground and he has an amazing ability to see birds well above him in the sky. Bobby is super a?ectionate, energetic, food-motivated, eager to please and is very quick to learn new skills. He loves toys and chewy bones and will follow you everywhere, hoping for constant petting and attention. He sleeps well through the night. He is great with other dogs and seemed ok with cats in the shelter (although he is not living with them in his foster home). Bobby would make a great running buddy (needs continued work on the leash) but is not recommended for a home with toddlers or a person unstable on their feet as he is a bit rambunctious. At 46 lbs. he is all muscle and extremely ?t. His birthdate is estimated to be 8/1/23.

His ideal home would have someone who is home a lot (or who can take him to work), has a large fenced yard (or access to one on a regular basis) and is energetic. Another dog would be terri?c if it were con?dent and about the same size and energy level. I doubt that cats would work.
Please read our expectations before applying.

He will need a human who is knowledgeable about hounds and who will be willing to spend time to continue to make him the awesome dog that he can be.

Contact generalinfo@furryfriendsnetwork.com for questions or if issues are encountered with the adoption application or general adoption process.

Foster Homes are desperately needed in order to help more animals like this one. Please consider opening your heart and home to a homeless animal. To find out more about becoming a Foster Parent, see our website at www.furryfriendsnetwork.com. Look under VOLUNTEER tab.

name: Raven
description: Raven has been with her family her whole life. Unfortunately, their home burned down and is a complete loss after...
full_description:
Raven has been with her family her whole life. Unfortunately, their home burned down and is a complete loss after a wildfire in their rural community. They’re staying with family now, and the apartment they’re moving into doesn’t allow dogs Raven’s size. We’re desperate to find a new home for Raven where she can continue to be a loved family member.

Raven is being fostered with adult dogs of various sizes and she gets along with them. Her family has three children ages 4, 9 and 17 so has grown up with them. She is potty trained and walks well on a leash. She is content to just hand out and doesn’t require a lot of walks. She is happy and full of love to give.

Raven is an English Bulldog and American Bully mix. She weighs 55 pounds, and she is 5 years old.

Raven has been spayed, vaccinated for DHPP, Bordetella and rabies. She is also microchipped and is current on flea/tick and heart worm prevention.

She can arrive in New York on March 29. If you are interested in adopting, please fill out the application found here: https://throwadogabone.org/adopt

We respond to all inquiries. If you submit an inquiry, please check your spam folder.

name: Chaka Khan
description: Chaka Khan - This "Sweet Thing" came to us from the trailer park.  It was a very cold and rainy...
full_description:
Chaka Khan - This "Sweet Thing" came to us from the trailer park. It was a very cold and rainy day and she was roaming looking for food. Her tail looked like it was injured. The caretaker offered her food and she came running.
We asked a resident if she belonged to someone and they said that they moved away and left her behind. We held her as we said "I Feel For You" and "Ain't Nobody" will ever do that to you again.

We took her back to our office and we spayed her only to find out she was pregnant already. She was very thin. She went to foster care where she is acclimating to other cats, but she said "I'm Every Woman" and I'd rather be the only cat in a household because I've already been "Through the Fire" with other cats and I want my very own human being.

She is ready to commit to her human and has that look that says "Love You All My Lifetime"

Chaka is about 3 years old, she's a small and quiet girl. Look at her cute and worried face.

This is what her foster mom had to say about her:

"Chaka Kahn has been friendly with people since the moment she came into the house. She loves to be petted and to be showered with attention. She may not have had a lot of toys where she came from since she doesn’t seem interested in them presently, we are working on that skill. She is wary of other cats but the cats in the household are trying to get her used to them. Not sure how she will react around dogs but with cats she just stays her distance. But she loves people. If you want a kitty that you can love and who wants to spend time with you, Chaka is your girl."

If interested, please email Mirna at Mirnabowman.cdc@gmail.com
614-471-9000
Must be 24 or older.
Adoptions to Central Ohio homes only.
All dogs and cats in the home must be spayed/neutered.
Adoption Fee $100.00.

name: Jerry
description:
Meet Jerry! (came in with Ben)

This dynamic duo came to us recently and boy, do they have a true...
full_description:
Meet Jerry! (came in with Ben)

This dynamic duo came to us recently and boy, do they have a true zest for life. Energetic and playful, these two would make the perfect family doggo’s! They can be a bit jumpy so we’re not sure how they’ll do with small children but they are the sweetest pups who take treats gently and love to play! They came in together but also do lovely separate! We haven’t seen any separation issues between the two of them. They’re the sweetest boys and so ready to find their forever homes!


Here’s a few facts about our two scoops of happiness, Ben & Jerry!

(applies to both dogs)

Age - 1 yr

Size - Medium (55lbs)

Likes - Toys, Playtime, Fetch, Long walks.

House training - Both of these boys are housebroken and keep their kennel tidy, even overnight when they have to hold it longer!

Other dogs - Both of these guys have had great success meeting other dogs here at the shelter.

These boys are the sweetest treats around, if you think one (or both) might be the perfect match for you, fill out an application today to start the process!

**In Order to adopt an unspayed/unneutered dog from HSMC, You must live within an hour of the shelter. You will initially "Foster to Adopt" the dog and then the adoption will be finalized when they are brought back for their spay/neuter surgery. You will need to bring the dog back for vaccines and exams prior to their spay/neuter surgery**

Our adoption fees vary, Shelter Dogs are $180, Prison Dogs are $250, Puppies are $300, and Popular Pure-Breeds are $400. The price includes: a Home Again Microchip, set of shots, de-worming, heartworm testing (if old enough), spay or neuter, and a 1 year rabies shot (if old enough). All dogs adopted must leave with a county license at an additional cost of $21, this fee is cash only. Adoption fees can be done using credit card or cash. If you are interested in this dog, please call the shelter at 614-879-8368 or fill out an online application at www.hsmcohio.org

name: Odie
description:
adoption donation : $699

weight 55 lbs

Age 1 year old

Odie is an incredibly sweet and gentle family dog...
full_description:
adoption donation : $699

weight 55 lbs

Age 1 year old

Odie is an incredibly sweet and gentle family dog who gets along great with other dogs and currently lives with a cat whom he loves. He also lives with young children and is great with them.
Odie and his siblings were found abandoned in a rural part of Mississippi and one by one were sent to the northeast to loving homes. Odie is doing great in his foster home, but really needs a home of his own, with a yard for him to play in. He would love a home with another dog for company, but as long as someone is around to give him the love and attention he needs, he'd be fine as an only pet.

Odie loves toys and bones and is just a really good boy. He is completely house trained and knows how to sit and stay. He currently lives with small children and a cat and is great with everyone. Odie will make a wonderful family dog.

Wags is a struggling 501(c) 3 where one woman in rural Mississippi takes care of about 150 homeless and stray dogs. Adoption donations are the only source of funding for the rescue. Adoption fee includes the transport from Mississippi, vaccines, microchip and spay and neuter at one of the clinics we use.

For more information on adopting Odie or any of our Wags dogs please email mariaeftimiades@yahoo.com

name: Eli
description: Meet Eli, the adorable 5-month-old grey and white kitten who’s here to steal your heart with his sweet personality and...
full_description:
Meet Eli, the adorable 5-month-old grey and white kitten who’s here to steal your heart with his sweet personality and boundless energy! This little guy is the definition of a playful kitten—he’s always ready to chase after toys, pounce on anything that moves, and show off his acrobatic skills. But don’t let his playful side fool you—when he’s done running around, he’s all about snuggles and cuddles. Eli will happily curl up in your lap for some quality nap time or nuzzle up for a cozy cuddle session.

Eli is as friendly as they come, with a heart full of love for everyone he meets. Whether you’re giving him pets, playing with him, or just hanging out, he’ll be there with his purrs and cuteness, making sure you know just how much he appreciates you.

Since Eli is such a playful and social kitten, he would probably do best in a home with another kitty friend to keep him entertained and engaged. After all, who else is going to keep up with his endless energy and love for playtime?

If you're looking for a kitten who's sweet, playful, and full of charm, Eli is your guy! He’s ready to bring all his love and energy into a new home—could it be with you? Come meet this adorable little guy at the Petsmart Cherry Hill, NJ Adoption Center and see just how much joy Eli could bring to your life!

name: Romeo
description: Meet Romeo, an 11-week-old German Shepherd puppy who&#39;s ready to steal your heart! This little (but growing fast!) guy is...
full_description:
Meet Romeo, an 11-week-old German Shepherd puppy who's ready to steal your heart! This little (but growing fast!) guy is full of puppy energy, curiosity, and that signature shepherd intelligence.

As with any young pup, Romeo will need plenty of socialization, basic training, and guidance to grow into a well-mannered adult. He's still working on house training and all the puppy basics, so he'll need a family ready to be patient and consistent. Given his size already, Romeo is on track to be a large dog, so setting him up with a solid foundation now will be key.

If you're looking for a loyal, active companion and are prepared for the fun and responsibility of raising a shepherd pup, Romeo just might be your match!

If you're ready to adopt now and want to learn more about, meet, or adopt this pet, you can start the process in one of two ways:

Come on in during open adoption hours Tuesday - Saturday 12:30-3:00! For in-shelter pets (not in foster care) coming in ASAP is the fastest way to adopt.

**the below two methods are slower than visiting us**
Call us (413-781-4000 x 1) or email us (springfield@dakinhumane.org) for more information about a pet. We are often on the line with another client, but we return voice mail and emails within 24 hours.

All adult dog adoption fees include;
-spay/neuter
-rabies and kennel cough vaccinations
- heartworm test
-current parvo/distemper vaccines (may need additional boosters with your veterinarian)
-microchip implanted & registered to adopter

full_description:
Meet Juliet, an 11-week-old German Shepherd puppy who's ready to steal your heart! This little (but growing fast!) girl is full of puppy energy, curiosity, and that signature shepherd intelligence.

As with any young pup, Juliet will need plenty of socialization, basic training, and guidance to grow into a well-mannered adult. She's still working on house training and all the puppy basics, so she'll need a family ready to be patient and consistent. Given her size already, Juliet is on track to be a large dog, so setting her up with a solid foundation now will be key.

If you're looking for a loyal, active companion and are prepared for the fun and responsibility of raising a shepherd pup, Juliet just might be your match!

name: Christopher FIV+$99-IN FOSTER!
description: Meet Christopher, a guy with rugged good looks who is currently parking his paws in foster care. While he was...
full_description:
Meet Christopher, a guy with rugged good looks who is currently parking his paws in foster care. While he was shy upon arrival at Dakin, his foster says that he is settling in well. On night one, she discovered he has a BIG appetite and he mastered the fine art of litter box use quickly. The next morning he greeted her with a cute meow and allowed her to pet him. It looks like Christopher is starting to blossom, now that he's had a taste of the luxuries of indoor life. Christopher is FIV+ but this doesn't prevent him from being your next best friend!

Change is hard for this cat. This cat will be very nervous when you first bring them home. You will need to set up a room with a litter box, food, and water. It will take days for this cat to become comfortable and confident in the new home. This cat will be going home with a behavior plan that will need to be followed in order for everyone to transition successfully.

FIV is a cat-only virus and does not affect people or dogs. FIV+ cats most often live long, healthy, and relatively normal lives with no symptoms at all. FIV is not easily passed between cats. If you are looking to add an FIV+ cat to your family and you currently have cats that are not FIV+ please speak with your vet.

full_description:

Ce petit chat est zen et joyeux ! Il est plein de vie et roucoule de bonheur : il court, saute, grimpe et joue dans ses tunnels, monte sur l'arbre chats ou encore s'amuse avec ses petites balles. Il est curieux de tout et nous suit partout dans la maison. Il vient se coller contre nous, lorsque nous travaillons l'ordi, coutons la tl ou encore nous mettons au lit pour une sieste ou pour la nuit ! Il adore nous laisser caresser sa belle et douce bedaine tout en ronronnant abondamment ! Ce petit garnement est trs attachant et il embellit la vie du foyer dans lequel il vit. Vous craquerez vite pour lui et vous ne voudrez plus vivre sans sa belle prsence ! Charlot est trs gourmand et essaie de manger la nourriture de ses humains. Il faudra tre patient avec lui et parfaire son ducation ce sujet. Charlot est un chaton donc les frais d'adoption pour lui sont de 340$. Il est strilis, vaccin et micropuc. Il n'est pas test pour le virus de l'immunodficience fline (VIF) ni pour la leucose fline (FeLV), mais sa mre Chatouille est ngative pour ces deux virus. Des assurances sant de 6 semaines viennent avec son adoption. Vous pourrez avoir recours l'aide de l'quipe des adoptions aussi longtemps que ncessaire. Vous avez aussi droit une consultation vido gratuite de 30 minutes pendant les 3 premiers mois suivant l'adoption avec notre consultante en comportement flin FelineGood ( https://www.felinegood.ca ).

Afin d'avoir une chance de l'adopter, veuillez remplir notre formulaire d'adoption directement sur notre site web: https://www.reseausecoursanimal.org/nous-contacter/formulaire-adoption/

This little cat is zen and happy! He's full of life and coos with happiness: he runs, jumps, climbs and plays in his tunnels, climbs the cat tree or plays with his little balls. He's curious about everything and follows us around the house. He comes and snuggles up to us when we're working on the computer, watching TV or putting us to bed for a nap or for the night! He loves to let us stroke his lovely, soft belly while he purrs loudly! This little rascal is very endearing and makes life so much more beautiful in the home he lives in. You'll quickly fall in love with him and won't want to live without him! Charlot is very greedy and tries to eat his humans' food. You'll have to be patient with him and train him accordingly. Charlot is a kitten therefore the adoption fees for him are $340. He is sterilized, vaccinated and microchipped. He is not tested for feline immunodeficiency virus (FIV) or for feline leukemia (FeLV) but his mother Chatouille is negative for both viruses. You will also be provided with health insurances for the first 6 weeks following adoption. You will also have access to the support of the adoption team for as long as you need it. You will also have access to a free 30 minutes video consultation during the first 3 months following the adoption with our cat behaviour consultant FelineGood ( https://www.felinegood.ca ).

In order to get a chance to adopt him, please fill out our adoption directly on our website: https://www.reseausecoursanimal.org/contacts/adoption-form/

If you are interested in meeting a dog or cat, we require an adoption application. If the animal has "HAS APPLICATION" listed, they are still available to receive additional applications but also may be in the process of being adopted soon. Apply for a CAT: https://www.citydogsrescuedc.org/adoptable-cats.html

City Dogs & City Kitties Rescue is a foster-based rescue in Washington, DC. We do not have a shelter. CDCK has a thorough adoption process to find the best possible fit for each of our dogs and cats.

Upon accepting a new cat or dog into the organization, we provide a basic vet visit that includes necessary vaccinations, disease screenings, deworming, microchips, and spay/neuter for dogs six months and older. We do not provide a comprehensive medical exam before adoption. As a result, sickness, injury, and disability may exist unbeknownst to CDCK. City Dogs & City Kitties Rescue is not responsible for payment of any vet care, including known and unknown medical conditions once a cat or dog is adopted from us.

Cat specific vetting: Rabies, FVRCP. Cats are tested for FIV and when age appropriate, but not when born to a FELV/FIV negative mother in foster care.

Kittens have age-appropriate vetting to date, which includes deworming, microchip, and the first FVRCP vaccine. Kittens born in care to a negative mother will not receive a FIV/FeLV test. An adopter will need to agree to cover costs of spay/neuter when he/she is age-appropriate (usually 16-20 weeks) and will need to continue his/her kitten vaccines (including rabies) as he/she grows older. Kittens under 12 weeks of age must be adopted in pairs or to a home with friendly resident feline. They will not be considered as singles.

BIOGRAPH

Meet Meatball!

Meatball has been with his owners for 2 years and it is with heavy hearts that they must rehome him.

Overall, Meatball is sweet boy, but he has bitten his owners in the past so they have taken him to extensive training classes. He must wear a shock control some of his reactivity, however, now he has become reactive to the collar, so they are having a difficult time getting it on him.

Meatball requires a new owner who is familiar with the dachshund breed and understands their “quirks.” His new owner MUST be patient and COMMITTED to his ongoing training.

Meatball is neutered, housetrained, current on vaccinations and also crate trained, although he does not like anyone near his crate. He is okay with other dogs but has not been exposed to cats. Due to his reactivity and past history, NO children for this guy, please.

This handsome boy has a lot of love to give to the right EXPERIENCED owner. He is currently in Burlington County, NJ. If you feel you have the time, patience and commitment required to offer Meatball a stable and loving home, please submit your application via the following website: www.sophiasgracefoundation.org

Meatball is neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, and heartworm negative. He is currently in Burlington County, NJ and his adoption fee is $400.00.

name: Maxwell
description: Meet Maxwell. This handsome boy came to the shelter as a stray in December. Sadly with no owner stepping up...
full_description: Meet Maxwell. This handsome boy came to the shelter as a stray in December. Sadly with no owner stepping up to reclaim him, we must do our best to find him a new home. So far we have seen that Maxwell is a very happy and energetic boy who lives to be around people and other pups. He still has a very puppy like attitude and would do well in a home with another dog who is laid back but can still teach him the ropes. Since he is a very energetic dog, small kids are not an option. We feel that he would knock them over while he was running through a house trying to burn off some energy. Maxwell does needs a 6ft fence and someone with husky experience. If you think Maxwell would be a great addition to your sled team, please reach out.

name: Figgy Newton
description: Figgy Newton is so affectionate and just as sweet as a fig, with a little bit of nuttiness that she...
full_description:
Figgy Newton is so affectionate and just as sweet as a fig, with a little bit of nuttiness that she shows with her playful antics. She loves to rub her face across yours and give little kisses as she nuzzles your nose. She's a happy girl with a comfy bed and a window to look out all day long.

Figgy was found laying in the middle of the road on a hot summer day, seemingly unaware that she was in imminent danger. Our volunteer scooped her up off the hot pavement and took her home where she realized Figgy had an enormous eye ball that needed medical attention. She had a successful enucleation and makes one beautiful one eyed kitty with her silky black coat setting off the golden eye she still has. Her loss of her eye was no big deal, as she adjusted quickly and acts like a normal kitty.

Unfortunately, we learned that Figgy is FeLV (feline leukemia) positive. She's lucky that we were able to rescue her because she has a much better prognosis being an indoor only cat with the best environment to thrive. We've also done additional testing for Figgy and have determined that she has very low amounts of the virus which is even better news for her and her future family! Since Figgy Newton is FeLV positive she is not able to live with FeLV negative cats. We think she will be happiest as an only cat, so this shouldn't be an issue for her. She can also live with other FeLV positive cats but we are unsure how she will get along with them. We're happy to chat more about FeLV to ensure adopters have all of the information they need to feel comfortable adopting Figgy. She is currently healthy with normal bloodwork very recently and doing super well!

--


To be considered as a potential adopter, complete an adoption application at https://www.tailshigh.org/home/adoption-application/.

Completing the application does not guarantee it will be approved. We are an all volunteer group and unfortunately are unable to answer every phone call, adoption inquiry, or application. Please understand you will be contacted only if your application is approved.

name: 26-Donny Meowning
description: Meet Donny, a 6-month-old black and white kitten who is still learning to trust and open up. Rescued from an...
full_description:
Meet Donny, a 6-month-old black and white kitten who is still learning to trust and open up. Rescued from an uncertain situation, Donny is currently in a foster home working hard on his socialization. Though he's a little scared at first, he's making wonderful progress every day. With patience and time, he's starting to allow gentle pets and is beginning to understand that humans are a source of love and comfort.

Donny's unique tuxedo markings and soulful eyes make him absolutely adorable, and he has a sweet, gentle spirit just waiting to shine once he feels safe. While he may be shy right now, he's showing his true potential with the right encouragement. Donny will thrive in a calm, patient home where his new family can give him the time he needs to fully trust and feel secure.

If you're looking for a kitten with a bit of a challenge but a lot of potential, Donny might be the perfect fit for you. With a little love and understanding, he'll blossom into the affectionate companion he's meant to be. Come meet this shy but sweet boy--he's ready for his next chapter!This cat is waiting for it's Forever Home!

Email adoptions@ctcatconnection.org with a question or better yet, complete an application for quickest consideration. (Application: https://www.ctcatconnection.org/adoption-application/).

Please consider fostering a cat or dog by applying on our website.

A cat's behavior in the shelter is usually not what it will be like in your home; if the cat is nervous, anxious, or agitated, please know that a shelter is a very stressful place for a cat.

Kitten Policy: It is important to understand that the socialization of kittens with other animals as playmates is important for their development. Therefore, CT Cat Connection has a policy that kittens and teenagers up to 12 months of age are adopted in pairs unless there is another animal in the household as a playmate and companion.

Due to demand, we cannot place cats or kittens on hold. Your visit to the shelter is to meet any cat or kitten available for adoption at the time of visit.

If you or anyone you know is interested in helping the shelter, we are always looking for foster families of our cats and dogs, as well as in-person volunteers, to assist with animal care. Fill out an application, which can be found at https://www.ctcatconnection.org/get-involved/

name: Bash aka Jack Shay in foster
description: Meet Bash, a gentle 11-year-old cat who has found himself back at the shelter through no fault of his own....
full_description:
Meet Bash, a gentle 11-year-old cat who has found himself back at the shelter through no fault of his own. His previous owner had to return him due to allergies and a busy travel schedule, leaving Bash understandably confused and scared. He's currently a bit shut down at the shelter, but deep down, he's still the loving and affectionate cat he's always been.

Bash adores attention and snuggling--his favorite thing is curling up next to someone who will give him all the love he craves. With his calm, quiet nature, Bash would do best in a home where he can feel safe and secure, with someone who understands that he needs time to adjust. He may be shy at first, but once he gets comfortable, he will become the loyal and cuddly companion you've been looking for. His previous owner shared, "He's a wonderful conversationalist who will want to know all about how your day was and if you've been out and about." He would do well with older children or polite dogs but he has not told us if he wants to share his home with other cats.

This sweet senior cat deserves a second chance at a peaceful, loving home where he can enjoy his golden years. If you're looking for a calm, affectionate friend to share your quiet moments with, Bash could be the perfect fit. Come meet him and see how quickly he'll win you over with his heart of gold.This cat is waiting for it's Forever Home!

About Our Rescue Group:

The St. Mary's Animal Welfare League is a nonprofit, rescue organization that specializes in the rescue, care and placement of abused, neglected and homeless companion animals. Our animals are vaccinated, microchipped, spayed or neutered and receive medical treatment before being placed in carefully selected homes. We strive to educate the community in areas of humane education and responsible pet ownership as well as helping to control the pet overpopulation in our area by promoting the spaying and neutering of all companion animals.

===Come Meet Our Pets:
Come meet our cats every Saturday from 10 a.m. to 2 p.m. located at Petco in California Maryland.
We also have a cat facility in Callaway. The Cat Castle Rescue Center is located in the Callaway Village Shopping Center and is open every Saturday and Sunday from 11am to 3pm.
Please contact info@smawl.org for appointments to meet our dogs.

===Our Adoption Process:
It is the St. Mary's Animal Welfare League's policy to attempt to place each of our rescued animals in a home that is well- suited to their needs. Once an animal is placed from our rescue, the animal cannot be sold, given away or otherwise transferred. If the adopter is, at any time, unable to keep or continue to maintain the animal for any reason, the animal must be returned to the St. Mary's Animal Welfare League.

We work hard at matching our animals to adopters, so they may end their search for a loving, permanent home. Temperament, special needs and personality are all factors in our placements.

===Step #1
The Adoption Application
The initial step in our adoption process is the Adoption Application. This can either be done online or in person. The Adoption form must be filled out completely including vet references and two personal non-family references. Your application will be reviewed and your references will be contacted. We contact your veterinarian to ensure that your current or recently deceased pets were properly taken care of---this means being current on all vaccinations and spayed or neutered. In order to speed up the process, please contact your veterinarian and let them know to expect our call.

===Step #2
Personal Interview You will be interviewed by a SMAWL Board Member or Volunteer either through phone, email or in person. This is an opportunity to learn more specifics about you, your family, your pets and the type of pet you are looking for. At this time, we may suggest that you consider a different animal---one that we may feel might be more acceptable for your situation. If you are completing your application in person, this will most likely be done at that time of completion.

===Step #3
The Home Visit If all goes well with the application verification, we will schedule a home visit. A home visit is required to ensure that your home is everything you say it is on the Adoption Application. It needs to be a suitable safe environment for your new pet. All pets and family members should be home at this time.

===Step #4
Meeting Your Potential Adoptee Once the Application has been reviewed and all references checked, arrangements will be made for you to meet with the animal you wish to adopt, either through the foster parent or the animal's Case Manager. As a courtesy to our foster families, we do not ask them to show their animals to individuals until we have completed the application approval process. If you have other animals, we recommend a neutral meeting place, such as PETCO or a local park to ensure the animals are compatible outside of their own territory.

===Step #5
Finalizing The Adoption Once the adoption has been approved, we will contact you to finalize the adoption. You will need to sign the contract and pay our adoption fee. (Young Dogs Under 1 =$300, Dogs over 1 = $250, Young Cats 2 years and under =$125, Older Cats over 2 years = $75)
Foster to adopt over a two week period may be available on a case by case basis.

Any applications received for adoptions from beyond St Mary's county line, will be subject to additional terms and conditions available on request.

Please Remember: Our entire organization is staffed by volunteers. We have NO paid staff. Our volunteers must work your application around their business and personal lives. We do our best to respond to all inquiries within 2-3 days, and most of the time we are able to respond within 1 day. Please be patient and thank the volunteers you meet for their service to our community's homeless pet population.
===
We Serve the Following Cities, Towns, and/or Counties:
We serve the Southern Maryland area.

Hi my name is Azalea! I am a shy cat looking for a patient owner who is willing to give me time to adjust and open up in my new home. Since I can be rather shy, I would prefer a quieter home without younger children. Once I get comfortable and learn to trust, I will come out of my shell and start to show more of my true personality. After all, the best things in life are worth waiting for - like a special bond with a cat who likes the calmer side of life.

I am currently under the care of the shelter medical team at HSHV. If you would like to learn more about me, please reach out to the Adoption Desk at (734) 662-5585.

I am currently under the care of the shelter medical team at HSHV, so I am not ready to go home just yet. If you would like to learn more about me, please reach out to the Adoption Desk at (734) 662-5585.

Bradley
Est DOB Mar 11-2024
Neutered, vaccinated including rabies, dewormed, microchipped

Meet him at Pet Valu, Stratford

Bradley is such a fun loving, adventurous boy. He is a snuggler who likes to snuggle in a night, or sleep right next to you holding your hand. He likes to sit with you or in your lap, asking to be pet and held.

He enjoys climbing his tall cat tree and cat climbing wall. He loves his toys and springs are his favorite! Bradley needs another cat in his new home or to be adopted with one of his siblings.

Email for an application: axelsimprintrescue@outlook.com

name: Eren
description: Eren is a bright-eyed, curious, and playful kitten. Born with a luxurious tuxedo coat, she is dressed and ready to...
full_description:
Eren is a bright-eyed, curious, and playful kitten. Born with a luxurious tuxedo coat, she is dressed and ready to be your plus one in your life adventures. This sweet pea enjoys chasing springs and felt balls around the house, climbing on the cat tree, and being a couch potato with her people. Her superpower is her easygoing, chill personality. Eren often snoozes through action movies, vacuum time, and parties while staying close to her feline and human buddies. She loves snuggles and kisses on her forehead!

Eren and her siblings, Armin & Mikasa, have blossomed in foster care, becoming happy, healthy, well-rounded kittens, and are ready to continue their adventures with their new families!

description: Faisca is a 3.5 yr old Portuguese Podengo who came to us 2 years ago from Portugal. In Portugal, many...
full_description:
Faisca is a 3.5 yr old Portuguese Podengo who came to us 2 years ago from Portugal. In Portugal, many dogs are used for hunting & then cast aside, like an old, used tool. Many end up living the rest of their lives in municipal pounds & never get to know what it's like to have a family. Faisca was one of the lucky ones.
Unfortunately after living comfortably with cats for the past 2 years, he's now decided that cats are no longer friends so we've agreed that he should be rehomed to a family with no cats.
Faisca is a very intelligent boy. He'll need a large fenced yard to run & play in with a 6 ft fence. Podengos are very agile & can usually scale shorter fences with ease. If you'd like to give him a forever family, fill out an application on our website! Copy & paste this page of our website, which explains the process of adoption with the link to the application at the bottom: https://seniorsighthoundsanctuary.org/the-adoption-process

name: Perseus & Pegasus (bonded pair)
description: These boys are shining stars, alright! Perseus and Pegasus have been lighting up their foster family’s life for the last...
full_description:
These boys are shining stars, alright! Perseus and Pegasus have been lighting up their foster family’s life for the last few weeks as they have really come into their own. They’ve shown us that their CH (cerebellar hypoplasia) is in fact mild, and really doesn’t slow them down one bit!

They’re a playful duo that can’t get enough of their toys, wrestling with each other, and zooming around after all of the things that roll! Their foster mom says wand toys, ball tracks, and anything round is sure to be their favorite new activity.

They’re also such an affectionate and cuddly pair. If you are looking for the sweetest souls, that will curl up on your lap and purr purr purr, Perseus and Pegasus are definitely your guys. While these sweet boys are just under a year old, they are the perfect blend of energetic and silly kittens, while having absolutely perfect manners, knowing when it’s time to chill out and relax. They are absolute angels while their foster family is at work, and eager to snuggle and play when they get home.

While their CH makes them a bit unsteady on their feet at times, they are able to get up on the couch with ease and can go up and down stairs, it just takes them a little bit longer. These boys have no real “special needs” as CH is not a progressive neurological disorder, meaning it won’t get better or worse, and it isn’t contagious to other cats, dogs or humans. They will have a perfectly normal life, just like any other kitty. They’re just a little wobbly and we think that makes them amazing!

We’re excited to share that Perseus and Pegasus are officially accepting adoption applications and we can’t wait to find them a forever home as a bonded pair. These floofy lover boys are simply the best!

---

description: Ginny is a 5 month old mixed breed puppy who just took her freedom ride from Texas! She, her brother,...
full_description:
Ginny is a 5 month old mixed breed puppy who just took her freedom ride from Texas! She, her brother, and mom were found in Texas as strays. They were suffering from mange and fleas and a rescue in Texas took them in, treated their mange and fleas, and nursed them back to health. Once healthy, they made their way to North Paw Rescue!

Ginny has an amazing personality and is super sweet. She loves to lay and cuddle with humans and is pretty calm for her age. She has a spunky personality and has fit right in with her doggie foster siblings that range from sizes small to XL. She was shy at first but is coming out of her shell quickly! She is often found wagging her tail and giving kisses. She is currently being crate trained and knows how to sit as well. She is doing well with potty training, but will need to continue this in her forever home. She is a very sweet girl who loves to play and then spends a lot of time resting. She is a wonderful puppy and would do well around other dogs and kids. Though she has not been cat tested yet, she has not had much of a prey drive and would likely do well with cats, which she can be exposed to at a meet and greet to make sure. She is a wonderful puppy and will make a family very happy!

Ginny's adoption fee is $600, which includes: her alter, a microchip, her rabies and age appropriate DAPP vaccines, flea/heartworm preventative, and a deworming treatment while in foster care.

If you think she may be perfect for you, please apply using the link below!

https://www.cognitoforms.com/NorthPawRescue/NorthPawRescueDogAdoptionApplication

**Unfortunately, we cannot adopt out to Canada at this time.

full_description:
Meet Annika!

Annika is a 2year old stunning American Staffordshire Terrier mix with what we believe to be Catahoula Leopard Dog. She was found as a stray in the Rio Grande Valley of South Texas with her two puppies, who have since been adopted. Now, it’s Annika’s turn to find her forever home!

This gorgeous girl has a truly unique look—her coat is a soft champagne color with striking leopard spots, and her fur feels like cashmere. She has one mesmerizing blue eye and the other a warm amber, making her beauty impossible to miss.

Annika is strong and muscular, but don’t let that fool you—she has a playful, puppy-like side and thinks she’s a lapdog! She will happily crawl into your lap, melt into you, and soak up all the love and attention she can get.

She enjoys the company of other dogs with proper introductions and is ready to bring joy to a loving home. Annika is full of love and waiting for her perfect match—could that be you?

If you’re looking for a sweet, affectionate, and beautiful companion, Annika is your girl! Apply to adopt her today!

description:

We were rescued along with our sister Shrimp and...
full_description:
Hi, my name is Minnow and this is my brother Guppy!

We were rescued along with our sister Shrimp and brother Anchovy after we were dumped in the woods in Philly. The only silver lining is that we were dumped around the corner from our foster mom's house. She dropped everything to bring us in when someone reached out to her.

I was very frightened at first, as was my brother Guppy. Since being in foster care, I have made amazing progress. Poor Guppy is still a bit nervous. He is also a Siamese (a handsome flame point at that). I will come up to you for pets, but I would be best in a home without children since I have a funny way of asking for more pets. And that is to slap your hand—I don't mean to be aggressive, I am still learning to cat! I know Guppy would continue to make progress in a low-key home as well.

I am so so playful and have a lot of energy. I am still a kitten after all! Guppy is equally as playful and we both love dinner time and Churu treats. It's a fantastic way to bond with us, especially with shy guy Guppy.

Lastly, I love to sleep cuddled up to my foster mom, and I am not afraid to greet guests.

It would be so incredible if a patient and understanding person would give both me and Guppy a home together. Someone who gets cat behavior and can help Guppy and me come along even more.

We are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, combo-tested negative for FIV/FeLV, and microchipped. We are ready for our happily ever after!

Could you be the special and unique someone we have been dreaming of?

name: Bane
description: Hi! My name is Bane! I am pretty new at the kennel and the staff/volunteers are still getting to know...
full_description:
Hi! My name is Bane! I am pretty new at the kennel and the staff/volunteers are still getting to know me, but here is some basic information: I'm about 9 months old and weigh 43 lbs. I am a sweet, curious and playful pup! I am looking for my forever home so if you think I may be your new best friend, please visit the website to request a meet: www.tinyurl.com/meetacitydog

Visit: 9203 Detroit Avenue Cleveland, OH 44102

Fee: $61 | Includes spay/neuter, shots, microchip, license,

The CITY DOGS mission is to increase adoptions from the City Kennel by changing the image of the pit bulls who make up the majority of the kennel population, by preparing all adoptable dogs in the kennel for lives in loving homes and by creating as many opportunities as possible for the public to meet and get to know our dogs for the terrific pets they are meant to be.

Our Adoption Process...
Here's a little about how things work:
All of the CITY DOGS posted for adoption are available for direct adoption from the kennel, unless noted otherwise. You must schedule a meet with a dog in advance - we are not currently accepting walk-ins. Please look online first to see if there are any dogs you think would be a good fit for your home before scheduling a meet. To get the process started, visit www.tinyurl.com/meetacitydog and fill out the form. One of our adoption counselors will get in touch to schedule and confirm your meet! At the kennel, an adoption counselor will introduce you and your family to the adoptable dogs, share information we know about them, and discuss our suggested ways for successfully integrating a new dog into your home. You are welcome to meet multiple dogs. If the dog you adopt is already fixed, he or she may leave with you that day - otherwise, the dog can go home after receiving the spay or neuter surgery.)

About Our Dogs: All available dogs have gone through a behavioral and medical assessment. This assessment is a snapshot of who the dog is at that given time. We cannot make any guarantees with regard to behavior, temperament or health of any City Dog once they are in the home. Most of our dogs are picked up as strays, so we do not know what kind of home environment they were living in (i.e. with kids, other dogs or other cats), nor do we know if most of them are house trained. Everything we know about them is based on volunteer and staff observations. We do have some dogs in foster homes, where they will have more information about how the dog is in a home environment. It is very hard to tell with certainty whether or not a dog will be good with kids, cats or another dog. If you have kids in the home or another dog, we do require that they be present for a meet and greet with the dog you are considering for adoption.

Heath/Vaccinations: Dogs that are adopted directly from the kennel need to go to your personal vet within two weeks of leaving the kennel. All dogs receive their DAPPL, Rabies, and Bordatella vaccines, though you may be required to get follow up boosters. All dogs come microchipped and with a Cuyahoga County license.

full_description: Meet Dilly Dilly, a puppy with a heart full of courage and a spirit brimming with playfulness. This little guy's energy is contagious, making every day feel like an adventure. He's smart, quickly learning how to potty train and keep a clean kennel. Dilly Dilly loves everyone he meets, greeting them with a wagging tail and friendly bark. His bravery is inspiring, facing every new experience with a determined, playful demeanor. Dilly Dilly's intelligence and energy make him the perfect companion for active families. He loves to wrestle dogs and humans alike, and when not doing that, he's playing with his favorite tennis ball. His friendly nature ensures he'll be a wonderful addition to any home. Adopt Dilly Dilly and experience the joy of a loyal, loving friend.

full_description: Meet Hickory Dickory, a puppy with a heart full of love. He's an intelligent little fellow who's quick to learn new tricks, making him a joy to train. His mellow demeanor is a calming presence in any home, and he's always ready for a cuddle session, a trait that makes him a perfect companion for quiet evenings. His friendly nature makes him a hit with both humans and fellow canines alike. Sweet as a summer's day, Hickory Dickory's charm is undeniable. His loving, gentle spirit is a testament to his resilience. Adopt Hickory Dickory and fill your life with unconditional love and companionship.

name: Ghost Project
description:
Meet Ghost: Your Ultimate Snuggle Bug

Introducing Ghost, a charming 1-year-old cat who will melt your heart with his affection...
full_description:
Meet Ghost: Your Ultimate Snuggle Bug

Introducing Ghost, a charming 1-year-old cat who will melt your heart with his affection and playful antics. Affectionately called Ghost, he is a total snuggle bug who takes a little time to warm up to you, but once he does, he will melt right into you and even sleep next to you in bed.

Ghost is a purring machine and loves to groom his humans, showing his affection in the cutest way possible. He loves getting into mischief with the resident cats, often trying to open the treat jar together. Ghost is super playful and enjoys spending time with both dogs and cats in the household. He doesn't seem to mind kids and is overall a friendly and sociable cat.

Although Ghost can be a little skittish while acclimating to a new environment, he loves being around people and is always ready for some cuddles. He came to the rescue with an old injury that required his tail to be amputated, but he has healed very nicely. Now, his tail-less charm is just one more detail that adds to his unique and endearing personality.

If you're looking for a loving and playful companion who will bring joy and warmth to your home, Ghost is the perfect match for you.

Interested in adopting Ghost? Submit an application on www.sfcva.org today to give this sweet boy the loving forever home he deserves!

name: Dance Monkey
description: Dance Monkey is grooving to an adoption event near you! He has been in foster care with his siblings, and...
full_description:
Dance Monkey is grooving to an adoption event near you! He has been in foster care with his siblings, and around other dogs and cats. He has done very well learning how to play and his foster is working diligently with him to make use of the puppy pads!! Apply at sfcva.org today to meet him!

Adoption fees are $250 for an adult dog, $350 for puppies, and $150 for a senior dog. Cats are $150 for kittens, $125 for adults, and $75 for seniors. Adoption fees can be made via cash or credit/debit card.

If you are looking for an adult dog, please remember to bring a martingale collar and non-retractable leash with you the day of the adoption, or be prepared to pick one up at Petsmart at an adoption event! If your preference is a feline, please bring a carrier, or cardboard carriers are available at events for $10.

We have adoption events every Saturday at one or more of our area Petsmarts, and are often out and about in the community as well. Events are posted on our Facebook page at www.facebook.com/squishyfacecrewva. Animals that do not have an individual meet and greet set up will be at these open adoption events; you do not have to have an application on file to attend. If there is a particular pet you are interested in meeting, please submit an application in advance at www.sfcva.org. We accept applications until 8pm every Thursday for individual meet and greets.

We try to respond to all applications within 48 hours, but please be patient - we are 99% VOLUNTEER POWERED, and most of our hardworking volunteers have full time jobs outside of rescue as well.

Follow us on Facebook and Instagram: @squishyfacecrewva

Thank you for considering adoption!

name: Darla
description:
Meet Darla! 

If you&#39;re looking for a heart full of love wrapped in the cutest, wrinkliest package, look no further...
full_description:
Meet Darla!

If you're looking for a heart full of love wrapped in the cutest, wrinkliest package, look no further than Darla! This darling girl came to us as a stray, but it didn't take long for us to realize she's nothing short of amazing. Darla's speckled ears, sweet wrinkly white coat, and adorably silly overbite make her one-of-a-kind, but it's her loving, joyful spirit that truly makes her unforgettable.

Darla may be hard of hearing, but that doesn't slow her down in the least! She's got a big heart and a zest for life that's completely contagious. Whether she's sniffing around on a walk, wagging her tail in delight, or cuddling up with you on the couch, Darla just wants to be by your side, sharing all the love she has to give. One of Darla's favorite things in the world is spending time with her people. She's an adventure-seeker at heart and would love to join you on walks, trips to the park, or even just enjoying a leisurely afternoon in the backyard. And after a fun adventure, she'll be the first to snuggle up for some quality lap time, showering you with affection and kisses. Her gentle, easygoing nature makes her a joy to be around, and she'll make you smile every day with her sweet personality and silly little quirks. Darla is an absolute lovebug who just wants to be the best companion she can be, and she'll make a lucky adopter the happiest!

Could you open your heart and home to this delightful girl? Darla is ready to bring all her love and joy to the right family. If you're looking for a playful, affectionate, and endlessly loving companion, Darla might just be the match for you. Come meet this sweet girl today, and let her show you how much love she has to offer!

Dogs: Darla is seeking a home without canine companions.
Cats: We have no history about Darla with cats.
Children: We have no history about Darla with children.

Visit our Adoption Center during our Winter Hours to meet your potential new best friend! We're open Tuesday through Friday from 1 PM to 4 PM and Saturday from 12 PM to 4 PM. Adoptions are on a first-come, first-served basis, so be sure to check our website for details on the adoption process. We look forward to seeing you soon! Thank you!

name: Bilbo Waggins
description:
Meet Bilbo Waggins! 

Bilbo Waggins is a delightful older gentleman with a heart full of spunk and a nose that...
full_description:
Meet Bilbo Waggins!

Bilbo Waggins is a delightful older gentleman with a heart full of spunk and a nose that never stops! Bilbo came to us as a stray from the community and we've found that he has a charming personality and zest for life. He's sweet, social, and always ready to make a new friend! With a love for leisurely strolls and the thrill of exploring new scents, Bilbo is the perfect companion for your daily adventures.

Bilbo dreams of nothing more than a cozy couch to call his own and a warm lap to curl up on after a day of sniffing and strolling. With his sweet nature and playful spirit, Bilbo is sure to brighten your days! Could your home be the place where Bilbo finds his happiness?

Dogs: Bilbo is dog social. If you have a dog at home, we'll arrange a meet-and-greet before you head home.
Cats: Bilbo's history with cats is unknown.
Children: Bilbo's history with children is unknown.

Visit our Adoption Center during our Winter Hours to meet your potential new best friend! We're open Tuesday through Friday from 1 PM to 4 PM and Saturday from 12 PM to 4 PM. Adoptions are on a first-come, first-served basis, so be sure to check our website for details on the adoption process. We look forward to seeing you soon!

name: Sugar
description: This is Sugar! She's about 2 years old and has been waiting for her family to adopt her for quite...
full_description:
This is Sugar! She's about 2 years old and has been waiting for her family to adopt her for quite some time. She's been at the rescue since she was a kitten. Many foster cats have come and left her foster home, and she often wonders if she's pretty enough, friendly enough, or what may be the reason no one has chosen her. We assure her that her time will come!

Sugar is a sweet girl who is happy to relax in a cozy spot on her own. She has incredibly silky soft fur. When she decides it’s time for affection, she will rub against your legs till you give her some scratches and she won’t want you to stop. She’s not big on playing with toys, but she does have a few she likes to randomly go after. She also loves the cardboard cat scratching boards. Sugar is very easy going and low maintenance and just needs a quiet cozy spot to land.

Fostered in Cuyahoga Falls, Ohio!

name: Prissy
description: Sweet Prissy is 4 or 5 years old and is blind. The vet at Virginia Tech said it is probably...
full_description:
Sweet Prissy is 4 or 5 years old and is blind. The vet at Virginia Tech said it is probably genetic. You wouldn't know she can't see except that she moves around somewhat cautiously.
She knows where her food and water bowls are and uses the litter box perfectly. She was spayed after having a litter of kittens when she was very young. Right now she sleeps a lot. Her caretaker feels like she needs a home where she can get some activity with someone that can help her have a better life.

full_description:
