My name is Emma! I was born the day after Thanksgiving to an accidental litter, lovingly referred to as the "FRIENDS Litter". My mama presents strongly as a black lab, but is reportedly a mix of shepherd, rottweiler, and bully. My dad is a coonhound mix. I am going to be a big girl, but my heart is just as big! My foster paw-rents said I am definitely the lover girl of the litter. I am ready to bring lots of snuggles into my new home!

I AM GREAT WITH...
Other dogs and children!

I AM STILL WORKING ON...
Potty training & crate training. I have not been exposed to cats.

MY VETTING...
I am spayed, microchipped, dewormed, on preventatives, and have initial vaccinations. My adopter can bring me back to COPAW's vet clinic between 3/31/25 - 4/7/25 to have my shots boosted at no expense.

name: Kai
description:
ABOUT ME... 
Hi. My name is Kai. I was surrendered to the Marion pound when I was maybe 8 weeks...
full_description:
ABOUT ME...
Hi. My name is Kai. I was surrendered to the Marion pound when I was maybe 8 weeks old. I love my treats, my foster family, playing with my foster brothers and cuddling with my foster mom. I sometimes sleep with the tip of my tongue hanging out, which my foster mom thinks is adorable. I will cuddle up with a foster brother to nap, too. I love hanging outside in our fenced yard with my foster family. I really enjoy tug toys, and chew toys. I have cats in the house and for the most part, I just check them out.

I AM GREAT WITH...
People, guys and gals. I haven't met a stranger because everyone loves me at first sight! I am great with sleeping in my crate at night or when my fosters have to leave. I am not afraid of any sized dog either so I'm great with other dogs.

I AM STILL WORKING ON...
House training since I am still a baby. When my foster mom is paying attention, I go outside really well...but I still need a lot of patience and practice. I cannot go all night without potty breaks or I will go in my crate. I still need some help realizing that shoes aren't chew toys if you leave them on the floor in my reach. I don't have much exposure to kids. Since I am a baby, I want to jump on kids so they will pet me and I will need some training.

I AM NOT GOOD WITH...
Leash training, yet! I like having control so not good with a leash but I am food motivated enough that I should learn quickly.

**All animals in our care are spayed/neutered, microchipped, heartworm tested (age 1 & up), given preventatives, and provided with initial vaccinations AT MINIMUM. Booster shots are included in the adoption fee and will be performed at our clinic, or the adopter can use their own vet at their expense. Adopters must reside within 2 hours of Columbus, OH. No transportation assistance is available.**

name: Lulu
description:

full_description:
ABOUT ME...
Hi, I'm Lulu! I'm a sweet 7-year-old Beagle/Blue Heeler mix with a heart full of love. Though I recently lost my owner, I'm bravely adjusting to this new chapter with a wagging tail and a hopeful heart. I love being outside - sniffing, exploring, and soaking up the sunshine is my favorite way to spend the day. When the adventures are over, I'm all about snuggles and cozy nights in. I am fully potty trained and have no need with a crate, as I never chew on anything I'm not supposed to!

I AM GREAT WITH...
Kids! I'm gentle and patient, and I love having little humans to keep me company.

I AM NOT GOOD WITH...
I'm still figuring out how I feel about some new experiences, so a calm and understanding home would be best while I continue to adjust.

I AM STILL WORKING ON...
Getting used to new routines. I've only ever known life with my previous owner, so I'm learning how to feel comfortable in different environments.

I REQUIRE...
Lots of outdoor time! A home with a yard or someone who loves taking walks would be a dream come true for me. And, of course, plenty of love, patience, and belly rubs.

**All animals in our care are spayed/neutered, microchipped, heartworm tested (age 1 & up), given preventatives, and provided with initial vaccinations AT MINIMUM. Booster shots are included in the adoption fee and will be performed at our clinic, or the adopter can use their own vet at their expense. Adopters must reside within 2 hours of Columbus, OH. No transportation assistance is available.**

description: Hi! My name is Odie ! I am pretty new at the kennel and the staff/volunteers are still getting to...
full_description:
Hi! My name is Odie ! I am pretty new at the kennel and the staff/volunteers are still getting to know me, but here is some basic information: I'm about 8 months old and weigh 29 lbs. I am a sweet, curious and playful pup! I am looking for my forever home so if you think I may be your new best friend, please visit the website to request a meet: www.tinyurl.com/meetacitydog

Visit: 9203 Detroit Avenue Cleveland, OH 44102

Fee: $61 | Includes spay/neuter, shots, microchip, license,

The CITY DOGS mission is to increase adoptions from the City Kennel by changing the image of the pit bulls who make up the majority of the kennel population, by preparing all adoptable dogs in the kennel for lives in loving homes and by creating as many opportunities as possible for the public to meet and get to know our dogs for the terrific pets they are meant to be.

Our Adoption Process...
Here's a little about how things work:
All of the CITY DOGS posted for adoption are available for direct adoption from the kennel, unless noted otherwise. You must schedule a meet with a dog in advance - we are not currently accepting walk-ins. Please look online first to see if there are any dogs you think would be a good fit for your home before scheduling a meet. To get the process started, visit www.tinyurl.com/meetacitydog and fill out the form. One of our adoption counselors will get in touch to schedule and confirm your meet! At the kennel, an adoption counselor will introduce you and your family to the adoptable dogs, share information we know about them, and discuss our suggested ways for successfully integrating a new dog into your home. You are welcome to meet multiple dogs. If the dog you adopt is already fixed, he or she may leave with you that day - otherwise, the dog can go home after receiving the spay or neuter surgery.)

About Our Dogs: All available dogs have gone through a behavioral and medical assessment. This assessment is a snapshot of who the dog is at that given time. We cannot make any guarantees with regard to behavior, temperament or health of any City Dog once they are in the home. Most of our dogs are picked up as strays, so we do not know what kind of home environment they were living in (i.e. with kids, other dogs or other cats), nor do we know if most of them are house trained. Everything we know about them is based on volunteer and staff observations. We do have some dogs in foster homes, where they will have more information about how the dog is in a home environment. It is very hard to tell with certainty whether or not a dog will be good with kids, cats or another dog. If you have kids in the home or another dog, we do require that they be present for a meet and greet with the dog you are considering for adoption.

Heath/Vaccinations: Dogs that are adopted directly from the kennel need to go to your personal vet within two weeks of leaving the kennel. All dogs receive their DAPPL, Rabies, and Bordatella vaccines, though you may be required to get follow up boosters. All dogs come microchipped and with a Cuyahoga County license.

name: Petunia *tripod*
description: PLEASE NOTE: This dog is currently out of state but will be transported to Massachusetts shortly with no additional travel...
full_description:
PLEASE NOTE: This dog is currently out of state but will be transported to Massachusetts shortly with no additional travel costs. Roughly 90% of our dogs are adopted prior to their transport up to MA and 10% are adopted locally.

Meet Petunia! Petunia is approximately 3 years old, 21 lbs currently, and she may have some Beagle in her mix. She was found as a stray with an injured foot that ultimately had to be amputated. In her foster home, she is working hard on her house-training, crate training, and leash walking. She could go to a home with kids 5+, and other dogs. She has not been exposed to cats.

Her foster says, "Petunia is a special girl with a beautiful gentle soul. She has the happiest smile on her face all the time and lights up the room when she walks in. Her recent amputation has not slowed her down one bit! She runs circles around the others! Petunia absolutely loves other dogs she would thrive in a home with a furry siblings of her own. She loves to run and play but at the end of the day she enjoys to flop on the couch upside down and snooze by your side. She is the best little girl who aches to just be a part of a family."

She is available for adoption in N Dartmouth on March 24th. Please fill out an application on our website at https://www.browndogcoalition.com/adoptable as a first step.

-Dogs may not be given as gifts or surprises.
-Please thoughtfully discuss with your entire household the physical, safety, financial and emotional responsibilities of a dog BEFORE applying to adopt.
- More information about our adoption process, application and adoption fees can be found at browndogcoalition.com

full_description:

If you are my human I will love you and be loyal forever - I adore people big and small. I am fully house broken, I take treats gently and will sit if asked. I also walk like the true gentleman I am on a leash - walking the hood with my person is so much fun! While I am the friendliest of fellows, I would prefer a home where I am the only fur-bearing mammal because, truthfully, I am greedy and prefer all attention stays on me, and me only. I am a star-dog, after all. My foster family is in Houston, Texas and I am available locally or in the Northeast, where most of my BDRP buddies travel to. If interested in adopting yours truly, please be speedy and complete an application. I can’t wait to join my forever family!

All cats receive one or more vaccinations, a basic veterinary examination, are dewormed, and spayed/neutered. Cats over 3 months of age are microchipped and FIV/feline leukemia tested.

Upon adoption, all cats must go home in a carrier. You may bring one of your own or purchase one from FAPL. Please remember, the carrier cannot be opened until safely within your home.

name: Ragu
description: Meet Ragu, a stunning long-haired German Shepherd Dog (GSD) who is currently in foster care in East Haven, CT. Ragu...
full_description:
Meet Ragu, a stunning long-haired German Shepherd Dog (GSD) who is currently in foster care in East Haven, CT. Ragu is a remarkable dog with a sweet temperament and a playful spirit, making her a wonderful companion for the right family.

Ragu came to us from Dallas Animal Services, and since her arrival, she has truly blossomed in her foster home. She is known for her affectionate nature and is particularly good with older kids and other dogs, showcasing her friendly demeanor. However, due to her high energy levels and playful enthusiasm, we recommend that she is placed in a home with older children who can engage with her in positive and constructive ways. Ragu can be quite excited when meeting new people, and her exuberance is a testament to her loving personality—she truly is a love bug!

As a German Shepherd, Ragu has specific needs that require an active and committed owner. This breed thrives on physical activity and mental stimulation, so she will do best with someone who enjoys outdoor adventures, playtime, and regular exercise. Understanding the unique traits of GSDs is essential, as they are intelligent dogs that require consistent training and socialization.

Ragu has already undergone obedience training, which means she has a solid foundation of basic commands and manners. With continued guidance and positive reinforcement, she has the potential to become an even more well-behaved and well-adjusted member of the family.

If you’re looking for a loyal and loving companion who will bring joy and energy into your life, Ragu might be the perfect match for you. Let’s work together to find her the forever home she truly deserves!

name: Bonnie
description: Meet Bonnie &amp; Clyde - The Dynamic Duo Ready for Their Forever Home! This lovable brother and sister pair of...
full_description:
Meet Bonnie & Clyde - The Dynamic Duo Ready for Their Forever Home! This lovable brother and sister pair of kittens are ready to steal your heart! This dynamic duo is inseparable, sharing a bond that's as sweet as it is strong.

Clyde is a stunning orange Buff kitten with silky fur and the most endearing little face. He's got a gentle voice, a social nature, and a deep love for cuddles. If you're looking for a kitten who will snuggle up and purr contentedly in your lap, Clyde is your guy.

Bonnie, his beautiful sister, is a gorgeous gray and white tuxedo with silky fur and mesmerizing eyes. She's just as playful as her brother, and together, they love to wrestle and chase toys around. When playtime winds down, Bonnie and Clyde love nothing more than curling up together (or with their favorite human) for a cozy nap.

These two are the perfect companions-full of love, energy, and affection. They are both spayed and neutered, microchipped, have age-appropriate vaccines, and are house-trained with good litter box manners.

Bonnie and Clyde are looking for a forever home where they can continue to share their lives with a loving human (or family) who will cherish them and give them the attention they deserve. If you're ready to welcome this sweet pair into your home, they're ready to bring joy and love to your life.

name: Chase
description: If there were a contest for the World's Friendliest Cat, Chase would surely be a contender.  Chase, about a year...
full_description:
If there were a contest for the World's Friendliest Cat, Chase would surely be a contender. Chase, about a year and a half old, was one of about 15-20 cats taken out of a hoarding situation. You know that (inaccurate) stereotype of cats being aloof? Well, that's definitely not Chase! He immediately recognized that his foster mom was being nice to him, and he showed himself to be an affectionate boy who responds to petting with a warm purr. His foster mom describes him as a playful, affectionate boy and a bit of an attention whore, so he would do best in an interactive home where he will get lots of play time and not be left unaccompanied for long periods of time. As you can see in one of the photos, he readily flops over for belly rubs. We have not observed him with dogs or kids; we think he would do well with kids who know how to treat a cat respectfully. Chase's sole potential downside is that he is an early riser who tends to become active before dawn, and who tends to be vocal about it. He seems to be an easy lap cat who would be suitable for a suitably early-bird first-time adopter.

He has been:
- neutered
- given rabies and distemper vaccinations
- tested negative for FeLV and FIV
- treated for worms and fleas

His adopter will receive his medical records and an explanation of them. There is a simple adoption process and an adoption fee so we can continue to help cats in need. He's being fostered in Medford.

Cats can live up to 20 years, so give careful thought to the changes that are likely to occur in your life during that time. If you can and will commit to him and provide a safe, loving home for life, then respond to RoyCBarrows@gmail.com. Please include your phone number for a faster response and say a little about yourself and the home you would provide for him, as we try to match people with the right cats.

full_description:
My name's Morticia, and I'm looking for a new family who will help me trust again. My former owners have left me with some emotional scars, and I will need a patient and loving new family to help me overcome my past.

I was literally thrown into the lobby of the shelter in a carrier. Because of this trauma it has taken me some time to learn that the people here at Heal are only here to help me. I've started to come out of my shell and trust again, but I'll need my new family to help me continue on this journey.

I'm up to date on vaccinations, spayed, and I have tested negative for feline leukemia.

I'm looking for an adult only home where I can adjust and love my new family in my own time.

If you have the patience and love to help me overcome my past, please come meet me at Heal.

Meet Zip and Rocky!

Zip and Rocky are two bonded brothers who are looking for their forever home. They are both approximately 3.5 years old and have spent their entire lives together, so they must be adopted as a pair.
Both dogs enjoy going on walks, but they would really prefer a fenced yard where they can play freely. While walks are enjoyable, having the freedom to run around in a yard is even better! Like typical siblings, they may squabble occasionally during playtime, but their love for each other is unmistakable.
It's important to note that Zip and Rocky will not do well in a home with cats or other dogs, so we are seeking a household that does not have any other pets.
They are both house-trained and crate-trained, making them great companions for the right family.

The adoption fee for Zip and Rocky is $1,000.00, which includes their health records. Both dogs have been vaccinated, heartworm tested, neutered, microchipped, and have had dental cleanings.

name: Bunny
description: This is what we&#39;ve learned so far: She really, really wants to be with her people. She seems to be...
full_description:
This is what we've learned so far: She really, really wants to be with her people. She seems to be a little "velcro", She will make a great companion dog but might not do well alone all day with people who work outside the home for long hours.
She seems to be dog friendly and has been nose-to-nose with our pups through the baby gate and our fence line regularly. No issues and no signs of aggression whatsoever. She wags her tail and seems to really want to play. Thus the continued need for separation until she heals. If we remember to let her out about every 3 hours there are no accidents. She whines and tries to tell you when she needs to go. We think she knows the phrase "want to go potty outside?" means. No accidents overnight. She doesn't know "sit", "stay" or "lie down" commands. We will work with her on some basics after she fully heals.
We have an enormous crate and I tried setting that up in our family room when we were watching movies together this weekend. We learned that she is not a fan of kennels and "freaked out" inside it. I would not advise the use of a kennel with this dog. She was trying to dig her way out and clawed at the sides.

name: Bentley - available March 23
description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Calling all Chocolate lovers:
Bentley will be available March...
full_description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Calling all Chocolate lovers:
Bentley will be available March 23. Bentley is a 3 year old 91 pound neutered male chocolate lab that was surrendered because his owner worked long hours and didn't feel he was giving him what he needed.
This goofy tootsie roll loves everyone cats, kids and other dogs.

Please visit our website for more info on our adoption process and adoption application www.barkdogfarm.org

Please be sure all family members are in agreement to adopting and your family is ready to bring dog home now.

Applicants must be at least 21 years old. We do not have blanket criteria regarding adoptions. Each applicant is considered based on many things including but not limited to breed experience, yard ( visible fence preferred) and other animals in home. We try to avoid dogs with same sex households as pyrs typically do not do well with the same sex.

A volunteer will be in touch to discuss your application and the dog to determine if it is a good match. Your vet and two references will be called. A virtual home visit done. Once approved a meet and greet at the farm will take place. If all are in agreement an adoption contract will be signed and adoption fee paid. Adoption fees for dogs are $450. for adults over 12 months, $550 for puppies 12 months and younger. Fees for seniors, special needs or harder to place dogs will be determined by our Board of Directors. All dogs will be altered when adoption is finalized. This may involve young puppies be given until a certain age to be altered. All animals are up to date on age appropriate core vaccines, negative for parasites, heart worm and lyme tested if 6 months or older, microchipped and have a current health certificate. Proof of a basic obedience course completed is part of our adoption contract within six months.

Our descriptions are based on shelter evaluations, input from foster homes and interactions with our volunteers but are in no way a guarantee of temperment.

We show animals by appointment only. This is usually done meet outdoors so please dress accordingly.

Please email barkingdogfrm@gmail.com with any questions or to arrange a meet and greet.

description: Scout is a spirited 3-year-old solid black cat with an unbridled zest for life, perfect for an active household that...
full_description: Scout is a spirited 3-year-old solid black cat with an unbridled zest for life, perfect for an active household that can match his energy. This dynamic boy thrives on mental stimulation; he's a master at chasing wand toys, loves scaling multiple cat trees, and enjoys bird-watching videos or the real thing from the safety of indoors. Regularly rotating his toys will keep him engaged and entertained. Plant lovers beware, Scout has a taste for greenery, so ensure your botanicals are cat-friendly, or better yet, divert his attention with some irresistible cat grass or catnip. He's also a fan of sipping from sinks and faucets, adding a touch of whimsy to his hydration habits. While Scout plays a bit rough with other cats, he's a joy to have around for those who appreciate his lively antics and charming quirks.

This sweet-natured girl is looking for a forever home where she can continue to enjoy her favorite pastimes in comfort and love.

name: Rigby
description: 3-year-old Rigby is so much fun! Rigby is a friendly, silly boy. This playful, energetic dog would love to find...
full_description:
3-year-old Rigby is so much fun! Rigby is a friendly, silly boy. This playful, energetic dog would love to find an active person or family to play with. His favorite toys are tennis balls! Rigby is very treat-motivated, which will come in handy for positive reinforcement training! He's already working on sitting politely with his friends here at Lollypop, and he is eager to learn more!

We don't know if Rigby has a history of living with other animals, but here at the shelter he has really enjoyed playgroup with other dogs! As far as humans go, we recommend ages 6 and up due to Rigby's high energy level. We'll introduce all the people and dogs in the household to Rigby before sending him home, and give you tips for slow at-home introductions to any cats you may have. Could Rigby be the dog you've been searching for? He's waiting for you!

name: Calliope
description: Meet Calliope! This gorgeous girl is about 3 years old and just under 50 pounds. Calliope is quite shy, but...
full_description: Meet Calliope! This gorgeous girl is about 3 years old and just under 50 pounds. Calliope is quite shy, but she has opened up to several staff members here over time. Once she warms up, this sweetheart loves getting pets and attention. If you've been looking for a dog to curl up on the couch with, Calliope could be for you! Calliope is more confident with her best friend Andromeda by her side, so they hope to find a new home together. They've been waiting to find their new family since October - could it be yours?

tags: Lived with Cats or Small Animals
name: Nala
Tucker
description: Say hello to Tucker! Although we don&#39;t have any official DNA info, he appears to be some sort of shepherd...
full_description:
Say hello to Tucker! Although we don't have any official DNA info, he appears to be some sort of shepherd with the floppiest of ears!

We don't have much history on Tucker's life before he came to Lollypop Farm. However, this lucky pup is staying in one of our amazing foster homes so we are starting to learn a lot about him! Here are some fun observations:
-he does well with the other dogs in his foster home
-seems to be housebroken, and does let you know when he needs to go out
-walks great on leash
-fascinated by squirrels, but is polite about it
-loves to be near his foster mom and sleep with her

So if you are looking for a well-mannered young gentleman, Tucker may be right for you! Please email Hannah at hhecht@lollypop.org to schedule a meeting.

name: Andromeda
description: Andromeda is out of this world! This cutie is about 5 years old and weighs just under 50 pounds. She...
full_description: Andromeda is out of this world! This cutie is about 5 years old and weighs just under 50 pounds. She has a habit of leaving the tip of her tongue sticking out, and we think her "bleps" make her even more adorable! Andromeda is a playful, snuggly girl who LOVES getting tons of pets and attention from her people. She can be a little nervous when first meeting new friends, but once she warms up she's very affectionate. Andromeda and her best friend Calliope are a bonded pair and would love to find a new home together. They've been waiting to find their new family since October - could it be yours?

name: Diego
description: Meet Diego! This shy little guy may take a moment to warm up to you, but once he does, you&#39;ll...
full_description: Meet Diego! This shy little guy may take a moment to warm up to you, but once he does, you'll see just how sweet he really is. With his gentle purrs and playful spirit, Diego is sure to steal your heart. He's looking for a loving home where he can feel safe and cherished. Are you ready to welcome this lovely feline into your life?

name: Sparkly
description: Sparkly is a beautiful 2 year old gal that came to FAPL from a loving home. She’s a true sweetheart...
full_description:
Sparkly is a beautiful 2 year old gal that came to FAPL from a loving home. She’s a true sweetheart that just dreams of being loved once again. Sparkly lived with Meadow (also available) and they ADORE one another. Let’s help Sparkly find a wonderful home and feel loved.

No appointment is necessary to adopt. Adoptions are done on a first-come, first-served basis. Applications will not be accepted in advance and will be filled out at the shelter upon adoption. We want you to meet the purrrrfect feline for you and your lifestyle! FAPL is open Tuesdays-Saturdays from 11am-6:30pm. Sundays 12:00-3:00pm. Closed to the public Mondays.

All cats receive one or more vaccinations, a basic veterinary examination, are dewormed, and spayed/neutered. Cats over 3 months of age are microchipped and FIV/feline leukemia tested.

Upon adoption, all cats must go home in a carrier. You may bring one of your own or purchase one from FAPL. Please remember, the carrier cannot be opened until safely within your home.

name: Rosey
description:
Meet Rosey!

Rosey is 2 years old and currently 35lbs (although she could drop a few winter pounds).  Best guess,...
full_description:
Meet Rosey!

Rosey is 2 years old and currently 35lbs (although she could drop a few winter pounds). Best guess, no guarantee, is that she is a Bassett (or Dachshund?), mixed with something fluffy - Spaniel/Aussie/Collie perhaps??

Rosey is a great adjusted gal - good with kids and good with other dogs. Cat test can be facilitated.

Rosey is crate trained and potty trained-as with any rescue dog (or any dog for that matter), she may need a refresher course for a few days once she is in her new environment.

She is spayed, up-to-date on core vaccines, heartworm tested negative, dewormed, current on flea preventative, and microchipped!
____________________________________________________________________
**If you are interested, YOU NEED TO APPLY. Also, a follow-up email to info@safeatlast.net is strongly recommended.
____________________________________________________________________

To pursue adoption, please register on www.safeatlast.net. (Click Register on the left-hand side of our homepage.) When you receive your password on your email account, please log back on to our website to complete the SAFE AT LAST on-line adoption application. (Click Forms/Application on the left-hand side of our homepage and select the Adoption Application.) Once we have your completed application, if we feel you are a good match, we will contact you by email. (So, please check your SPAM.) Our process is straightforward but involves a phone interview, reference checks and a home assessment. An adoption fee of $450 applies.

YOU CANNOT MEET OUR RESCUE ANIMALS UNTIL YOU HAVE BEEN APPROVED TO ADOPT. WE CANNOT CONSIDER YOU UNTIL YOU HAVE SUBMITTED THE FULLY FILLED OUT SAFE AT LAST ON-LINE ADOPTION APPLICATION. Delay in submitting your application will put you behind other potentially suitable applicants. Ultimately, approved adopters will be required to complete an adoption in Schoharie/Albany County.

Thank you for your interest.

(Sorry, we will not respond to generic "check the box," "Is s/he available," "Can you give me more information" inquiries.)

NYS Rescue Registry No. RR 087

name: Little Red
description:
To learn more about Little Red, please get in touch with dogs@lostdogrescue.org.

Little Red will be attending one of our...
full_description:
To learn more about Little Red, please get in touch with dogs@lostdogrescue.org.

Little Red will be attending one of our adoption events coming up this weekend! To learn more about our upcoming events and to see which event he will be attending, please visit our event page at https://www.lostdogrescue.org/events/. (*Please note that the specific event pages are typically updated on Fridays with information on which dogs will be attending each event.*)

Meet Little Red, who's got a big heart! This sweet, affectionate 2-year-old Corgi mix loves nothing more than being close to his person for lots of love and all the pets he can get on his gorgeous red coat.

Little Red may not know many commands, but he's a great leash walker. He calmly enjoys his strolls and happily sniffs while out and about. He also enjoys meeting new people and other dog pals, but not in an overly excited manner.

Though he's not super food-motivated and can take it or leave it when it comes to treats, Little Red is an enthusiastic lover of hugs and tummy rubs. He gently jumps up on his short, little legs for some attention and will lean in for all the affection he can get. He's fine with being handled and is just a huge fan of cuddles.

With his gentle, warmhearted demeanor, this lovable low rider would thrive in a home where he's given all the adoration and snuggles he craves-Little Red just wants to be your best friend!

If you're searching for a devoted companion who just wants to be by your side, then Little Red is the guy for you-come meet him today!

name: Pinto
description: Meet Pinto! A fun-loving cat with a great personality. Pinto is always ready to offer a comforting purr or a...
full_description:
Meet Pinto! A fun-loving cat with a great personality. Pinto is always ready to offer a comforting purr or a playful pounce. He loves chasing wand toys and climbing onto shelves, but is happy to get as many pets from his humans as they will offer. Pinto would be a great addition any home where he can continue to have adventures and make memories.

To learn more about how to adopt Pinto, please fill out an adoption application (https://www.shelterluv.com/matchme/adopt/LDAC/Cat) or email questions to cat.adoptions@lostdogrescue.org.

name: Isabella
description:
To learn more about Isabella, please get in touch with dogs@lostdogrescue.org

Isabella will be attending one of our adoption events...
full_description:
To learn more about Isabella, please get in touch with dogs@lostdogrescue.org

Isabella will be attending one of our adoption events coming up this weekend! To learn more about our upcoming events and to see which event they will be attending, please visit our event page at https://www.lostdogrescue.org/events/ (*please note that the specific event pages are typically updated on Fridays with information on which dogs will be attending which events*

Isabella was surrendered from a commercial breeder. She was no longer wanted, and had no place to go. Isabella deserved better, so we opened our doors and hearts to change that for her. She is an adorable, special little dog who has endured quite a lot on her way to the safety of Lost Dog & Cat Rescue Foundation. She is looking for a family with abundant patience, love, and an understanding of her needs to help her be a wonderful companion - and your best friend forever. She would especially enjoy the company of another dog to show her how much fun being a part of a family can be!

Meet Isabella, our bravest of little warriors! Isabella is a small dog looking for a loving forever home that can match her relaxed energy and provide her with all the affection and support she deserves.

Isabella has come to us from a rough situation and is still adjusting to her new life, so a period of acclimatization is to be expected. She is still a little scared at sudden movements and new experiences, but her resilience shines through in her progress. She is tolerating handling and pets, if done slowly, and does not mind being picked up. This is important for Isabella because she is still getting used to going through thresholds, like doors, stairs, and other confined spaces.

She has done well on leash, and likes to walk around sniffing all the wonderful smells. Her favorite activity though, is playing around with her doggy pals. She will need slow introductions to larger dogs, but has been doing well with smaller dogs that match her size. A loving, slow, quiet home with another dog to lead the way, and show Isabella she is safe is sure to benefit as she continues to blossom out of her shell and becomes the best dog! Don't miss out on Isabella, your investment will lead to a big payout!

name: Maggie
description: Meet Maggie! She&#39;s a sweet, playful kitten who will demand your attention and love. Although she may be a little...
full_description:
Meet Maggie! She's a sweet, playful kitten who will demand your attention and love. Although she may be a little shy at first, Maggie will quickly warm up to you with some encouragement, pets and treats - she especially loves to chase after wand toys, and make biscuits on a cat bed. Maggie has done well with other cats, and would make a great companion in any home!

To learn more about how to adopt Maggie, please fill out an adoption application (https://www.shelterluv.com/matchme/adopt/LDAC/Cat) or email questions to cat.adoptions@lostdogrescue.org.

name: Zephyr
description: Meet Zephyr, the sweetest cat around! Zephyr is known for his friendliness and curious nature, and he&#39;s always ready to...
full_description:
Meet Zephyr, the sweetest cat around! Zephyr is known for his friendliness and curious nature, and he's always ready to get pets or have his long fur brushed. Zephyr can also be playful - he enjoys joys chasing wand toys, little springs, and anything with catnip. While great with people, Zephyr would prefer to be the only cat in the home.

To learn more about how to adopt Zephyr, please fill out an adoption application (https://www.shelterluv.com/matchme/adopt/LDAC/Cat) or email questions to cat.adoptions@lostdogrescue.org.

name: Costner
description: Hi I&#39;m Costner! I had a rough start to life but was luckily brought in to get life saving medical...
full_description: Hi I'm Costner! I had a rough start to life but was luckily brought in to get life saving medical care after fending for myself in the great outdoors! I feel so much better now and can't wait to find my forever family. I am the biggest lovebug and just want to be held or making biscuits in your lap. I love to lay in fuzzy beds and cuddle with my fellow cat friends. But prefer to be by your side at all times!

name: Gucci
description: Meet Gucci, the queen of confidence and the ruler of relaxation. This chunky, sassy lady may have a bit of...
full_description:
Meet Gucci, the queen of confidence and the ruler of relaxation. This chunky, sassy lady may have a bit of an attitude, but it only adds to her charm. She knows she's fabulous and expects to be treated accordingly! Gucci loves being in the spotlight-just on her own terms.

Head scratches are the way to her heart, and if you get it just right, she'll roll over and demand more. Despite her strong boundaries, she secretly adores attention and appreciates every bit of love that comes her way. When she's not soaking up pets, you'll find her in a cozy hideaway, lounging like the royalty she is.

If you're looking for a chill, independent, and slightly diva-esque feline to add some personality to your home, Gucci is your girl. Just remember: respect the queen, and you'll be rewarded with love (and maybe a dramatic flop for more pets).

name: Hashbrown
description: Meet Hashbrown, a little nugget of joy with a golden personality!! Hashbrown is a 27-pound young adult beagle mix. He...
full_description: Meet Hashbrown, a little nugget of joy with a golden personality!! Hashbrown is a 27-pound young adult beagle mix. He is a sweet, curious guy who loves to explore with his nose. He has the classic beagle coloring with chestnut, cream, and charcoal markings, some precious white toe-tips, and long, soft ears! Hashbrown is a medium energy pup, enthusiastic about a walk but equally ready for a nap in the sun. The best of both worlds! Hashbrown would like to remind you that allegedly breakfast is the most important meal of the day, so welcoming him into your life is practically a health move. Send in your adoption request today to meet a dog cute enough to be a snack!

name: Elmer
description:
*** AVAILABLE ON-SITE FRIDAYS AND SATURDAYS ***

Hi - I am Elmer! Instead of hunting wabbits, I am hunting for...
full_description:
*** AVAILABLE ON-SITE FRIDAYS AND SATURDAYS ***

Hi - I am Elmer! Instead of hunting wabbits, I am hunting for my forever family. I am incredibly sweet and well behaved. I love to snuggle up and cuddle. I have a great appetite and have been eating science diet dry food. I do well with other dogs - coexisting peacefully with a big dog pack while in foster. I have also been around 6 month old baby and was perfectly behaved - gentle and tolerant. I love to be near my humans and will find any spot to curl up and keep you company.

name: Celia
description: Celia may seem timid, but she is not shy about loving belly rubs and all of the attentions! This sweet...
full_description:
Celia may seem timid, but she is not shy about loving belly rubs and all of the attentions! This sweet female terrier mix is new to Saving Grace, but is clearly not new to loving on those giving her attention. With a few quick licks of her tongue, this beautiful white furred pup instantly melts you to her will.
Celia is an adult pup, weighing 45 lbs, and is looking for that person in her life to cuddle with forever. She would love some people to show her the ways of the world and increase her confidence with lots of experiences and reinforcement. Make an appointment to see Celia soon - she is sure to woo her next family soon!

name: Brom
description:
**AVAILABLE ON-SITE ONLY FRIDAYS &amp; SATURDAYS**

Some dogs come into our program with instant notoriety and rise to a celebrity...
full_description:
**AVAILABLE ON-SITE ONLY FRIDAYS & SATURDAYS**

Some dogs come into our program with instant notoriety and rise to a celebrity status quickly. Brom is definitely one of them. As a popular pup at Saving Grace, Brom would love to give back to his community by helping other Saving Grace dogs with major medical needs, our senior dogs, nursing moms, and those who need life-saving heartworm treatments. Through his adoption, Brom will ask his new family to assist him by making a donation of $500 (tax-deductible) in addition to the adoption fee ($395) to help his friends in need.

Brom is the cutest in the galaxy! While he might look like a little Ewok, Brom is a bouncy, sweet flirt who will steal your heart. He loves to give little kisses while snuggled next to you and getting his back scratched. Brom also has lots of energy for walks and playing, especially fetch. He's great with children and other dogs, and wants to make everyone his friend. Brom is almost completely potty trained, and while he is crate trained, he would prefer to be near you. He knows basic commands, but will need some gentle reinforcement to remind him of them. Adventure awaits...with Brom!

name: Elmo
description:
Elmo will be, indeed, so happy to see you!
This male black lab mix is not sure how he got...
full_description:
Elmo will be, indeed, so happy to see you!
This male black lab mix is not sure how he got here, but he sure is glad! With perky ears and a wagging happy tail, Elmo is happy to explore all the happenings around him - people, dogs and chickens! And when all that gets to be too much, he simply rolls on his back and gets some comforting belly rubs from the nearest volunteer.
Elmo is a puppy, and will quickly grow from his 35 lbs but his heart is already quite huge! If you think you can keep up with this furry animal, make an appointment to come visit today!

name: Marston
description: Who doesn&#39;t love a gentle giant? Meet Marston- the biggest and goodest boy around! Marston is a 97-pound adult mastiff...
full_description: Who doesn't love a gentle giant? Meet Marston- the biggest and goodest boy around! Marston is a 97-pound adult mastiff mix. He has a striking brindled coat, blending deep charcoal and rich caramel colors, and the sweetest brown "puppy dog" eyes. Marston is a big guy- he is strong and needs a fur-ever person who can keep up. That said, Marston is also a sweetheart and a shoo-in for the 2025 Mr. Congeniality contest. When he is out with the other pups Marston is the peacekeeper of the group and often makes gentle, appropriate corrections to his peers to remind them to play nicely and follow the rules. There is something so charming about walking by a tall fence and seeing sweet Marston's head pop up- this guy's size paired with his dazzling personality is truly a delight. If you have the strength and space to care for a big pup, send in your adoption request today. Marston will be so happy to meet you and we're warning you that you will be instantly smitten!!

name: Bear
description: How would you like to wake up in the morning and have a Bear-ista next to you, ready to help...
full_description: How would you like to wake up in the morning and have a Bear-ista next to you, ready to help you start your day? You're in luck! Meet Bear, the 50-pound adult retriever mix who will bring the pep you need to start your dayl! (Full disclosure: Bear is not fully trained in operating an espresso machine just yet...). Bear is a striking pup with a sleek cream and chestnut coat and luminous olive eyes. This sweetheart is a true athlete and would love a home where he could hike, run, and play with his fur-ever person!! Bear is always up for an adventure and is brimming with enthusiasm. If you're looking for a loving buddy who can keep up with your active life, send in your adoption request today!

name: Dixie
description: Meet Dixie, the pup who blends southern charm with tail wags and butt wiggles! Dixie is a 58-pound adult boxer...
full_description: Meet Dixie, the pup who blends southern charm with tail wags and butt wiggles! Dixie is a 58-pound adult boxer mix. She is a breathtaking pup with a sleek mahogany coat, deep brown accents on her face, expressive cocoa eyes, and some charming white toe-tips! Dixie can be a bit shy at first but she warms quickly. It is a delight to see her playfulness shine through! Dixie is an athletic pup but walks politely on a leash which will make it fun to take her on walks, hikes, and adventures. Send in your adoption request today to meet Dixie, the dog who is sweeter than a glass of iced tea on a hot summer's day!

name: Jack
description: George Clooney, Brad Pitt, Channing Tatum....all them hotties best move on over because Jack is in the house and he...
full_description: George Clooney, Brad Pitt, Channing Tatum....all them hotties best move on over because Jack is in the house and he has the charm of Jack Nicholson and the looks of, heck, he's better looking than anyone we can think of! Jack is a white Shepherd come husky mix who is an adult weighing about 66 lbs full grown. Jack is the consummate gentleman who adores people first and foremost and has great manners, not to mention has wowed all his lady doggo friends at the farm too. Jack would love an active home and folks who know something about his breed mix and the stimulation and exercise that will make him happiest. Jack is great in his crate and has been a star on the hiking team. He would do best with a female doggo companion if there is one in the home. Don't take our word on this one, come meet this drop dead gorgeous guy for yourself and see the total package!

name: Rosetta
description: Meet Rosetta, a bouquet of elegance, sweetness, and a bit of doggie silliness! Rosetta is a 38-pound adult shepherd mix....
full_description: Meet Rosetta, a bouquet of elegance, sweetness, and a bit of doggie silliness! Rosetta is a 38-pound adult shepherd mix. She has a striking look: a blend of light cream and blond fur, perky ears, and the sweetest deep brown eyes. This lady is playful, graceful and athletic! Rosetta is a leader on the trail and can keep up with all of your adventures! Rosetta loves people and is always up for a cuddle. Rosetta may have had a tough go of it but she is so ready to step into an easier life. She would love nothing more than a gentle fur-ever home where she can soak up some much needed love. Rosetta promises to deliver that love back ten fold! Send in your adoption request today to meet Rosetta, a pup sweeter than a rose!

name: Girlfriend
description: Watch out! Girlfriend will steal your heart (and maybe some snacks too!). Girlfriend is a young-adult 27-pound retriever mix likely...
full_description: Watch out! Girlfriend will steal your heart (and maybe some snacks too!). Girlfriend is a young-adult 27-pound retriever mix likely with some room to still grow. This beautiful pup has a (soft!) caramel colored coat, a cheeky white blaze on her sweet snoot and chest, and captivating charcoal highlights. Perhaps Girlfriend's most striking feature is the caramel "mask" around her loving, deep brown eyes. *swoon* Girlfriend is a bouncy, athletic, playful pup who would love a fur-ever home that is up for adventure and is as energetic as she is! Girlfriend loves to play with dogs and humans alike. She is friendly, fun, and a true sweetheart! Send in your adoption request today to meet Girlfriend- the pup who will make you believe in love at first sight!!

name: Douglas
description: Douglas is a medium-energy pup who enjoys playing with others dogs and definitely wants to keep up with his people....
full_description: Douglas is a medium-energy pup who enjoys playing with others dogs and definitely wants to keep up with his people. He is the first in his litter to wriggle his way into a person's lap and is great with kids. He sleeps quietly in his crate at night and occasionally naps or chews on dog toys in the crate during the day. Douglas enjoys being outside and has started leash training with enthusiasm. He is food motivated, which should make training easier. Enthusiastically affectionate, Douglas can't wait to go home with you!

name: Zoe
description: This sweet puppy is too beautiful and sweet to last at the Funny Farm for long! Zoe is a black...
full_description:
This sweet puppy is too beautiful and sweet to last at the Funny Farm for long! Zoe is a black lab mix, a healthy 29 lbs, with big soft ears and a bushy, happy, tail and perhaps some more room to grow.
She is curious around people and dogs, and will be mixing it up with her pals in no time! Still young, Zoe is eager to learn about all things suburban and is proving an attentive gal. Come check out Zoe and see if she is your next family member!

name: Carver
description: Carve out a little space in your heart and this mid sized low riding dude is going to be sure...
full_description: Carve out a little space in your heart and this mid sized low riding dude is going to be sure to fill it! Carver is a terrier mix who has that wiry hair and clearly mixed with something short and stocky that is less terrier and more mix. Carver arrived very shy and unsure but is getting settled in and more confident. He is a low key guy who has a great medium energy level as he is an adult and weighs about 38 lbs full grown. Carver is good with other dogs and has a neutral way about him that conveys comfort with dogs but he does not seem to prefer the throw down antics of the younger crowd. Carver is great in his crate and walks well on a leash. He has a coat that may be more low shed which makes him a highly desirable mix. Carver is ready to be the cut out you've been missing in your life up until now.

description: Meet sweet all-gray Slater! He can be shy at first, but warms up very quickly. He loves to play with...
full_description:
Meet sweet all-gray Slater! He can be shy at first, but warms up very quickly. He loves to play with string, all toys, especially his wand toy. Slater loves to be brushed and is great with other cats and came from a foster home with dogs. Slater was born around 06/03/2024.

For more information or to apply to adopt: https://www.anjelliclecats.com/adopt

name: Bowie
description: This dog is part of our shelter outreach program where we take dogs from overcrowded shelters in hopes of finding...
full_description:
This dog is part of our shelter outreach program where we take dogs from overcrowded shelters in hopes of finding them a forever home here! We generally do not have much background info on them and cannot guarantee they are housebroken. They are all up to date on vaccines, spayed/neutered and microchipped.

description: Callie and Piper are approximately 45 lbs each and both spayed females. They have a lot of energy and are...
full_description:
Callie and Piper are approximately 45 lbs each and both spayed females. They have a lot of energy and are very playful. The love playing fetch, catch & tug a war. They love all people including children. They are loving and looking for attention and love. They come from a single person household, which makes them push each other out of the way for attention at times. They both are food and treat motivated. They are very smart and quickly learned some commands: sit, sit up, stay, come, shake along with a few others including some hand signs.

They are used to a fenced in yard and love running around, exploring and sunbathing in it. They do walk pretty well on a leash, but due to a back injury I suffered they don't get walked on a leash much anymore. They get along with other dogs and do best with dogs similar in size to them. They are house and crate trained, but I don't keep them in crates. I do keep them gated off in their own bedroom, so the girls can play and sleep together while I'm away from home or sleeping.

They live with 3 cats, the dogs sniff and try to kiss and play with them. The dogs love their many toys. I do have their toys, blankets, treats and a large bag of dog food. They don't care for baths but do love to be brushed and are good about getting their toenails cut.

These dogs are located in Rochester, NY and are taking applications within 40 miles of the area. This is a courtesy listing, and all applications will be forwarded to their current owner. Please apply here: https://rescued-treasures.com/dog-application/

name: Casper
description:
Meet Casper

From his foster:
Casper (nickname we’ve been calling him is Hank, because once you meet him you’ll see...
full_description:
Meet Casper

From his foster:
Casper (nickname we’ve been calling him is Hank, because once you meet him you’ll see why!) is the kindest, most gentle giant you’ll ever meet weighing in at just under 70 pounds. This guy loves people! It doesn’t matter how long he’s known you or if you’ve just met, but he will come right over and lean into you for a hug. Truly the friendly and most affectionate dog I’ve ever met. He would really thrive with people who are home a lot and have a lot of time to spend with him. Hank LOVES to be outside and would love to have a backyard of his very own. He’s relatively low energy, so you’re more likely to catch him laying out in the sun than playing, but has excellent leash manners when it’s time for a walk. Indoors he is a perfect gentlemen, with great potty habits and is good in his crate as well. He’s pretty quiet, knows sit and working on “wait” and “come”, won’t chew/destroy your house and has stayed off the furniture so far. If you leave him out while you’re gone, he’ll just lay down and nap until you come back. He’s good in the car and extremely friendly with strangers.

I think Hank will be good with children, however he has a habit of “slapping” with the giant paw if you sit down and aren’t giving him enough attention, we are working on both “no” and ignoring him and it’s gotten better, however this is something we would probably want to mention to a family with small children just because of his size. He doesn’t jump and won’t knock a kid down if they’re standing, but will slap both paws on you if you’re sitting on the couch, which again could be too much for very small children. Maybe he would do best with kids like 6 and older? Behaviorally besides that I think he would be fine with kids and you can really do whatever you want to him, touch him all over, etc., and he doesn’t care. I also suspect he would be ok with other dogs, however we don’t have any dogs to test with. He did get a look of our outdoor cats, and was excited (not aggressive), so he could possibly go to a home with cats but would need a thorough introduction. Our cats are too feral and just dart when they see him, which makes him even more excited. He is friendly/non concerned with our horses, which makes me think he lived on a farm at one point.


Apply at www.caninehumane.org

An application must be filed before meeting any of our dogs or puppies.

What is included in our adoption fee:
*Age-appropriate vaccinations
*Deworming
*Lifetime Micro chip - no annual fee
*First Month of flea/tick prevention
*First Month of Heartworm prevention
**Spay/Neuter at our partner vet

The adoption fee is $350
Spay/Neuter is covered if performed at our vet partner facility.


Please note that puppies need to have human interaction every 3 hours.

Applications are required prior to meeting the puppy
.
Apply at: http://caninehumane.org/adoption-application/

Ash is a beautiful adult female that was brought to FAPL as a stray. She dreams of happiness in a loving home. Let’s give her that chance today! Come fall in love with your new feline best friend at FAPL!

No appointment is necessary to adopt. Adoptions are done on a first-come, first-served basis. Applications will not be accepted in advance and will be filled out at the shelter upon adoption. We want you to meet the purrrrfect feline for you and your lifestyle! FAPL is open Tuesdays-Saturdays from 11am-6:30pm. Sundays 12:00-3:00pm. Closed to the public Mondays.

All cats receive one or more vaccinations, a basic veterinary examination, are dewormed, and spayed/neutered. Cats over 3 months of age are microchipped and FIV/feline leukemia tested.

full_description:

Meet Rhonda!

Rhonda is approximately 8 months old, 36 lbs currently, and she may have some black mouth cur in her mix. She was found as a stray. In her foster home, she is working hard on her house-training, crate training, and leash walking. She could go to a home with kids 10+, and other playful dogs. She has not been exposed to cats!

Her foster says, "Rhonda is a love bug and loves any and all toys! She is still in puppy stage, so very energetic and enjoys playing with her doggie foster siblings. She is, for the most part, house trained as long as she is let out at regular intervals. She is fully crate trained. Rhonda knows basic commands such as "sit", "turn" and "down". When it's nap time or bed time, she will eagerly jump up and cuddle right against you to sleep. She makes the cutest little grunts when rubbing on her ears and petting her! She loves going out in our fenced in yard and running and playing with her other dog friends and humans! She will make a family (or individual) very happy and fill their heart with so much joy!"

She is available for adoption in N Dartmouth on March 14th. Please fill out an application on our website at https://www.browndogcoalition.com/adoptable as a first step.

name: Cassi
description:
Meet Cassiopeia!

A gentle and affectionate four-year-old Siberian Husky from Needham, MA, whose heart is as big as the sky...
full_description:
Meet Cassiopeia!

A gentle and affectionate four-year-old Siberian Husky from Needham, MA, whose heart is as big as the sky she’s named after. Wrapped in a stunning white and gray coat, Cassi is a quiet soul—well, except when the mail arrives! She takes her job as the household lookout quite seriously, offering a few barks to announce visitors. But once properly introduced, she’s all about love and companionship.

Cassi is an easygoing and well-mannered girl who enjoys the comforts of home. Whether you’re out for a few hours or just in the next room, she’s perfectly content and never stirs up any mischief. She’s crate-trained, house-trained, and already knows a few important commands like "come," "sit," "down," and "drop it." While she doesn’t have the signature Husky howl, she still has a strong presence, and her calm nature makes her a wonderful companion.

When it’s time to play, Cassi loves a good game of catch, a round of tug with her rope toy, or a nice walk around the neighborhood. She’s adaptable and flexible with routines, making her an easy fit for a variety of homes. While she hasn’t had many interactions with other dogs, she’s quite fond of cats and enjoys their company. The perfect pet sibling, perhaps?

One of the most charming things about Cassi is how much she wants to be a “good dog.” She’s the perfect mix of playful and relaxed, always ready for belly rubs and affection. She enjoys a lively home with familiar faces coming and going, though she may need a little time to warm up to new people. Men wearing dark sunglasses can make her a bit wary, but with patience and reassurance, she’s quick to build trust.

Cassi is healthy, vaccinated, spayed, and microchipped—ready to start her next chapter with a new loving family. If you’re looking for a sweet, loyal, and easygoing companion, she’s waiting to meet you!

If you're interested in providing Cassi with a loving home, please email adopt@joyfulpets.com for more information on adopting her! Please note that Cassi will remain with her current family until a suitable new home is found for her.

She is ready for a permanent good inside home with loving people.

name: Nefertiti
description: Nefertiti is a sweet, affectionate one-year-old calico girl with distinctive markings that seem to give her a permanent smile.  Nefertiti...
full_description:
Nefertiti is a sweet, affectionate one-year-old who was rescued as a pregnant, abandoned stray. She's a sweet calico girl with distinctive markings that seem to give her a permanent smile. Nefertiti thrives on attention and always welcomes people with warmth and friendliness. She adores being petted and will happily soak up all the affection she can get. Playful and full of energy, Nefertiti enjoys chasing toys and playing with other cats. She’s social and outgoing, making her a wonderful companion for both humans and fellow felines. We have not observed her with dogs or kids; we think she would do well kids who know how to treat cats respectfully. She can be adopted separately or with her son Puma (posted separately). Nefertiti would do best in an interactive home where she will get lots of play time and not be left unaccompanied for long periods of time. With her affectionate nature and friendly personality, she’s sure to bring joy and happiness to anyone lucky enough to adopt her. She seems to be suitable for a first-time adopter.

She has been:
- spayed
- given rabies and distemper vaccinations
- tested negative for FeLV and FIV
- examined by a vet and determined to be healthy.

Her adopter will receive her medical records. There is a simple adoption process and an adoption fee so we can continue to help cats in need.

Cats can live up to 20 years, so give careful thought to the changes that are likely to occur in your life during that time. If you can and will commit to her and provide a safe, loving home for life, then respond to RoyCBarrows@gmail.com-- this is the most direct way to proceed. Please include your phone number for a faster response and say a little about yourself and the home you would provide for her, as we try to match people with the right cats.

description: Bodie has such a beautiful coat! This very handsome boy is very sweet and very quick to purr. He loves...
full_description:
Bodie has such a beautiful coat! This very handsome boy is very sweet and very quick to purr. He loves cuddles, and will jump up in your lap to be petted. Bodie also is quite playful, loves to wrestle and romp with his sister Bronwyn, and is eager to play with balls and all kinds of other toys.

Bodie is for his forever home where he can feel safe and loved. Bodie would be happiest if there was another kitty in his new home he could play with. If you don't already have a kitty, Bronwyn would be an excellent choice - as he calls for her if she is out of sight too long. Bodie is great with children and other cats; we don't know if he has been around dogs, but think he would be fine with them.For more information or to apply to adopt, please go to: https://www.purrpartners.org/adopt/

name: Will O Wisp21
description: Will-O-Wisp had a very tough start in life. He was trapped by animal control from a home that was hoarding...
full_description: Will-O-Wisp had a very tough start in life. He was trapped by animal control from a home that was hoarding cats inside and outside their home. He was one of he unlucky ones that was forced to fend for himself outside. It must have been so terrifying for him. It is a testament to his courage that he survived at all. He had some access to food, but he was small and underweight when he came to us. His interaction with people was likely minimal. He is a little guy but is tough as nails. He loves other cats but is a little leery of humans right now. He has made great strides since he came into foster care. He accepts chin rubs, loves to rub your legs, marking you as his own. He even will come out and greet you when you come into the room. The purrfect home for him would be someone who has a friendly cat that will be his buddy and is willing to work with him in a small room until he gets comfortable. He wants to badly to interact - he just needs time and patience. Willie is a wonderful kitty.For more information or to apply to adopt, please go to: https://www.purrpartners.org/adopt/

name: Mia
description:
**Meet Mia - The Sweet &amp; Playful Husky Star!** 

Mia is a loving, playful, and oh-so-gentle Husky with a heart...
full_description:
**Meet Mia - The Sweet & Playful Husky Star!**

Mia is a loving, playful, and oh-so-gentle Husky with a heart as big as her personality! She **LOVES** car rides and will happily stick her head out of the window if you let her-though she prefers riding up front like the true co-pilot she is.

This sweet girl has an incredible ability to sense emotions-if you're feeling down, she'll come close to comfort you with her loving presence. She adores attention and wants to be the star of the show-whoever is giving her love instantly becomes her best friend, even strangers!

Mia is a quiet girl-she doesn't bark, but she will let out a **spooky, adorable whining noise** when she wants to be let inside. She's very gentle when taking treats and has a positive history with **dogs, cats, and kids.** She also does great at the groomers!

Housebroken and thriving with free roam, Mia is an easygoing companion-but be sure to pick up the trash because she may rummage through it! She loves all kinds of toys, especially stuffed animals, but don't bother with wet dog food-she's not a fan.

If you're looking for a sweet, caring, and fun-loving Husky to bring joy and comfort into your life, **Mia is ready to be your best friend!**

tags: Recommendation Older children due to fearful shy temperament that may be incompatible with young children
Requirement Only dog home due to a history of behaviors incompatible with a multidog home
name: Bossy
description:
**Meet Bossy - The Sweet &amp; Snuggly Loyal Companion!** 

Bossy is an affectionate, loyal girl with a heart full of...
full_description:
**Meet Bossy - The Sweet & Snuggly Loyal Companion!**

Bossy is an affectionate, loyal girl with a heart full of love! She tends to form a deep bond with one special person in the home but, once she warms up to others, she's all about snuggles and affection. She's always happy and eager to make new friends-especially outside, where she gets super excited to meet people!

A total car ride enthusiast, Bossy will try to hop in any car she passes (even parked ones!). She's also a peanut butter connoisseur and adores stuffed toys. One of her cutest quirks? She loves moving her dog bed from room to room so she can always find the perfect spot to relax.

Housebroken and crate trained, Bossy actually thrives with free roam and is a great listener. She knows several commands, including **Stay (with a "go" for release), Sit, Down, Come, Outside, and Go Potty.** While she's had positive interactions with kids, it's highly recommended that she go to a home with **older children** who understand to go slow with her due to her vision issues.

Though fireworks make her a little nervous, Bossy's love for her family shines through in every cuddle. If you're looking for a sweet, snuggly, and devoted companion, Bossy is ready to be your loyal best friend!

name: Rowan
description: Rowan is a gentle and timid soul who has endured a tough start in life, found as a stray and...
full_description:
Rowan is a gentle and timid soul who has endured a tough start in life, found as a stray and severely emaciated. Despite his past hardships, he has a heart full of love and is slowly learning that humans can be kind and caring. Though initially shy, Rowan adores gentle pets and affection, leaning into the warmth of a loving touch. Loud noises startle him, causing him to cower or retreat, but with patience and reassurance, he is gaining confidence every day. Rowan is searching for a compassionate home where he can continue to heal, feel safe, and be showered with the love and care he so deeply deserves.

Notes From Foster :

Meet Rowan! This sweet boy is the ultimate companion-he adores affection, loves to be pet, and will happily follow you wherever you go. He has a playful side but mostly just wants to be by your side, soaking up all the love and attention. Whether you're relaxing at home or out for a stroll, Rowan will be your loyal shadow, always ready for cuddles and companionship. If you're looking for a loving, devoted pup, he's the perfect match!

name: Big Mac
description: Big Mac is a lovable, gentle giant who was found as a stray but has shown nothing but sweetness since...
full_description: Big Mac is a lovable, gentle giant who was found as a stray but has shown nothing but sweetness since arriving here. This big boy thrives on attention and affection, always eager for pets and companionship. While he walks well on a leash, he does pull slightly, so a freedom harness is recommended to help with control. Despite his past, Big Mac has a warm and friendly nature, making him a wonderful companion for someone ready to give him the love and stability he deserves. Now, he's searching for a forever home where he can continue to share his affectionate heart and big-dog charm.

name: Rain
description:
**Meet Rain &amp; Sky - The Perfect Pair!** 

Rain and Sky are a sweet and friendly bonded pair looking for...
full_description:
**Meet Rain & Sky - The Perfect Pair!**

Rain and Sky are a sweet and friendly bonded pair looking for their forever home! They haven't been with us long, but their affectionate personalities have already won hearts.

Sky is the more outgoing of the two-he loves to be held and does well with other animals, even having a positive history with dogs. Rain is a bit shyer at first and may scamper away when visitors arrive, but curiosity always gets the best of him, and he'll peek out to see what's going on. Once he warms up, he adores head scratches and being held.

Together, they bring out the best in each other-Sky's confidence helps Rain feel safe, and Rain's gentle nature makes their bond even stronger. They have a great history with both kids and dogs, making them a wonderful addition to a loving home.

Could you be the one to give Rain and Sky their happily ever after?

name: Rylo
description:
**Meet Rylo**

Rylo is a super friendly and lovable shelter dog who adores everyone he meets! He&#39;s great with kids...
full_description:
**Meet Rylo**

Rylo is a super friendly and lovable shelter dog who adores everyone he meets! He's great with kids but does best with older children due to his high energy. Rylo is always up for an adventure and will happily go with anyone, especially if it means a car ride-just make sure to keep the windows up, as he prefers it that way.

This fun-loving pup is crate trained, housebroken, and thrives on a routine. He has a passion for toys, especially stuffed ones and balls, and he's a big-time ball chaser! Rylo even knows how to play fetch, making him the perfect companion for an active home. He's ready to find his forever family-could that be you?

name: Stella
description: Meet Stella! This beautiful bully mix is looking for a patient adopter to give her the soft landing she deserves....
full_description: Meet Stella! This beautiful bully mix is looking for a patient adopter to give her the soft landing she deserves. She can be a bit cautious with new people but is sweet and loving once she warms up. Stella has a positive home history with kids and other dogs, though she does resource guard from dogs and will need to be separated at mealtimes and with enrichment items. She loves to play with toys and will make a wonderful companion for a home willing to give her the time and care she needs to thrive. Could Stella be your new best friend?

tags: Requirement Adult only home as this cat is incompatible with children due to being easily overstimulated
name: Boudin
description: Boudin is a striking brown tabby with big, manly cheeks and an even bigger personality. Found as a stray, he...
full_description: Boudin is a striking brown tabby with big, manly cheeks and an even bigger personality. Found as a stray, he wasted no time charming the shelter staff with his affectionate and social nature. This handsome guy absolutely loves human company and will eagerly rub all over your legs, sometimes getting a little too excited in the process! While he enjoys attention, he can become overstimulated with too much petting, but the good news is he's easily redirected with a fun toy. Because of this, Boudin would thrive in an adult-only home where his affectionate, yet spirited personality can be appreciated. He's ready to find a loving home where he can play, bond, and be his wonderful, larger-than-life self.

name: Grimmie
description: Grimmie is a sweet but shy cat with a gentle nature. She&#39;s a little nervous around new places and loud...
full_description: Grimmie is a sweet but shy cat with a gentle nature. She's a little nervous around new places and loud noises, but with some patience and a few tasty treats, she'll quickly start to warm up. Once she's comfortable, Grimmie is all about big purrs and offering free biscuits. She has a great history with kids, enjoying their playful energy and always happy to join in the fun. While she did scratch the couch in her last home, providing her with proper scratching posts should easily solve the issue. Grimmie is ready to bring love and comfort to the right home!

name: Bacon
description: Hi, I'm Bacon. Strange name for a little girl, but hey... who doesn't like Bacon? I am a great helper....
full_description:
Hi, I'm Bacon. Strange name for a little girl, but hey... who doesn't like Bacon? I am a great helper. I will help you fold clothes, sweep the floor, and even do computer work. You see, I like to be with people and get all the attention I can get. My step has a bit of a scamper to it and my tail will switch in the air when I walk. Did I mention, I LOVE to be with people? My friends and I have fun together running and playing. My sharing of toys is very good. I have been told I make funny sounds when I sleep. Could be I am chasing mice or working on the laptop. Computer work can be so tiring. I smile in my sleep too, just check out my picture. Good thing I know when to take a cat nap. Close the computer and let us take a nap together.

Are you interested in adopting Bacon or another JCAPL pet you have seen? You'll need to start by completing an adoption application, available online at our website: www.jcapl.org. There is no obligation to adopt by completing an application, however, we do recommend submitting an application as soon as you find an animal you are interested in. We review applications in the order they are received.

Completed applications can be sent via email to adopt@jcapl.org , faxed to 919-300-5524 or delivered in person by visiting us at one of our adoption events on Saturdays at PetSmart in Garner (White Oak Shopping Center or Timber Drive next to Home Depot).

We will contact you as soon as possible once we receive your application.

Thanks for thinking adoption!
