description: Meet Noodles, this adorable orange and white boy is 1 years young, neutered, vaccinated, and ready to find his furever...
full_description: Meet Noodles, this adorable orange and white boy is 1 years young, neutered, vaccinated, and ready to find his furever new home with his future humans. Noodles was an owner surrender due to medical issues with his previous family. Noodles does have a history living with one other cats which he got along fine with. However, he has never lived with dogs or kids, so we think a home without either will fit him best and allow him to be more comfortable. If you are interested in adopting Noodles apply for him today!

description: FOUND 3/11/25, Wyandanch, case #25-110, male, contact Babylon Animal Shelter to identify/claim, 631-643-9270. If you are interested in adopting, you...
full_description:
FOUND 3/11/25, Wyandanch, case #25-110, male, contact Babylon Animal Shelter to identify/claim, 631-643-9270. If you are interested in adopting, you can come to the shelter, meet the dog, and then put in an adoption application. Up to 5 applications will be taken. Our strays are held 5 days by law and then they will get an exam, Heartworm test, microchip, and spay/neuter, and other medical procedures. Only once that is complete can they be picked up for adoption. You can expect it to take 1-3 weeks before a dog is ready for adoption.
For more information please call and speak with adoption staff.
631-643-9270

name: Nigel
description: Nigel is a cute young tabby and white male who is energetic and social. He loves people and attention. He...
full_description:
Nigel is a cute young tabby and white male who is energetic and social. He loves people and attention. He loves to know what you're up to, and will follow you everywhere. He's only vocal when complaining about something. Nigel can be picky about food, but right now he seems to like chunky wet food. Nigel has been very selective about other cats, so we think he would be best as a single.

Nigel is FIV and FeLV negative, neutered, and up-to-date on shots. Email adopt@kittykind.org to apply!

name: spencer and murphy
description: These two brothers have been together all their lives. They  are 7 and 9 thebrown one, spencer is quiet and...
full_description: These two brothers have been together all their lives. They  are 7 and 9 thebrown one, spencer is quiet and loves his bed.  The white one murphyis active gentle and polite, but has collapsing trachea and has bouts of a deep cough that can last 20 minutes.  Not often at night and they were much more frequent while he was settling in.  He also has a grade 4 heart murmur and a grade 4 patellar dislocation. He has seen the orthopaedic surgeon and the opinion is that the expected benefit from repair is outweighed by the anaesthetic risks. However he anoids standing on the affected right leg,, he does stairs well and loves outside,  he is not yet on meds but may need heart meds in the future. They are both pee pad  clean and are very nice little dogs .. they need a quiet home visiting children ok murphy does bark at strangers but soon recognises them.

name: Marshmallow! Sweet and cuddly!
description: Hi! My name is Marshmallow! I am a sweet, gentle and well behaved Great Pyrenees, 70 lbs, 3 year old...
full_description:
Hi! My name is Marshmallow! I am a sweet, gentle and well behaved Great Pyrenees, 70 lbs, 3 year old boy!
I am being fostered in Westport MA.
My family loves me and they describe me as really well behaved and gentle, hence my name which is very fitting!
They got me when I was only 2 months old but unfortunately their working schedule have changed and they feel really bad that I spend long hours alone at home waiting for my owners to come home, so although they are sad to have to say goodbye bye to me they want me to have the best family I could ever have as I deserve it. I will be staying with them until my new forever home comes along. I have being healthy all my life and Im neutered and up to date on all my vaccinations.
I love dogs all sizes and humans of all sizes as well!
I am good on a leash and ride great in the car. I am used to stay at home while I wait for my humans to come home without incident as I am not an anxious boy. I can also be crated but theres no need for that.
I am looking for a home where my humans can spend time with me during the day and give me the love and attention I deserve.
My rescue does foster to adopt. What that means is that the lucky family that wants to add me to their family has 2-3 weeks to get to know me before deciding if I am the right fit for their home. If I am not, my rescue will find me another foster to adopt up north asap.
My rescue thinks is best for my humans not to feel pressured to take a decision and need time to get to know me, and need time to add me to their routine to see if we are a match before making the life decision to adopt me.
If you are interested in me and want to learn about the foster to adopt process please visit my rescues website directly as Petfinder inquiries many times get lost into junk mail and don’t make it to our main email. Thanks!
Www.RociosRescues.org
RociosRescues@yahoo.com

full_description:
Breed: Boston Terrier mix
Sex: Male
DOB: ~12/05/2020
Weight: 42 lbs
Energy Level: Medium
Personality Type: Playful, Very Friendly, Active, Quick Learner
History: Transferred from animal control
Ideal Home: Any adult-only home with dogs!
Fence Requirements: Fence preferred
Special Info:

DOG APPLICATION: https://service.sheltermanager.com/asmservice?account=dr1937&method=online_form_html&formid=26

CAT APPLICATION: https://service.sheltermanager.com/asmservice?account=dr1937&method=online_form_html&formid=41

EXOTICS APPLICATION: https://service.sheltermanager.com/asmservice?account=dr1937&method=online_form_html&formid=46

The information we are providing for this animal was developed based on observations and assessments in a shelter or foster environment. We do our best to provide information that will help determine if the animal might be a good fit for you. Please note that behaviors may change in a home environment. We also ask our applicants to assume that any animal they adopt from us will need to be potty-trained and learn house manners, although this is not always the case. In most cases, the listed breeds are also a best guess. Our online animal bios are designed to provide as much information as possible and answer some anticipated questions. We do not have the resources to respond to emails with more specific questions.

We are receiving an unusually high number of applications at this time! Applications are reviewed as they are received, but we do not select adopters on a first-come basis. Our job is to ensure each pet is placed into the best fit home for them and that adopters are paired with an animal that is a good fit for their lifestyle. All animals will stay online until they are "pending adoption". Therefore, if an animal is still listed, we are still accepting applications for him/her! Please do not send inquiries about a specific animal's availability as this can change quickly over the course of the day. The fastest way to get a response is to simply submit an application! We will do our best to notify you by email if the pet(s) you are interested in are no longer available. New animals are posted daily, so please let us know if another furry friend peaks your interest (there is no need to fill out a second application)!

Fill out the application (DOG:https://service.sheltermanager.com/asmservice?account=dr1937&method=online_form_html&formid=44, CAT: https://service.sheltermanager.com/asmservice?account=dr1937&method=online_form_html&formid=41, EXOTICS: https://service.sheltermanager.com/asmservice?account=dr1937&method=online_form_html&formid=46) completely. Every question must be answered, and it must be signed.

-Applicants must be 21+ years old and live within a 50-mile radius of our shelter at 22415 Groesbeck Hwy, Warren 48089.

-You must identify at least 1 animal that you are interested in.

Once your application is received, it will be assigned to one of our volunteer Adoption Counselors who will follow-up with the applicant who is the best fit within a few days, or to discuss other options. It could take up to a couple of weeks for you to receive a final disposition on your application so there is no need to check on the status.

-Introductions will be scheduled by appointment only, 30 minutes per appointment. The entire household, including current dogs, must be present for the appointment. (Note: Please do not bring your dogs if you are meeting cats!). The introductions will take place outside in our parking lot (or in our cat room if you're meeting cats).

-We will perform vet checks for current and prior pets in the household.

-Finalizing the adoption will also be scheduled by appointment.

Thank you for your understanding.

full_description:
Breed: Great Pyrenees
Sex: Male
DOB: ~11/04/2022
Weight: 80 lbs - We are working on putting some weight on Thor. His healthy weight is closer to 100lbs. His breed is considered a Giant Breed and he is big in stature.
Energy Level: Medium
Personality Type: Friendly, Gentle, Loyal, Playful, Athletic
History: Transferred from another shelter
Ideal Home: This big boy needs space! He is best suited for a large fenced-in property where he can spend ample time outside, which he prefers and is most comfortable with. Great Pyrenees are bred to guard livestock so they are protective and loyal in nature - this fits Thor to a tee. Thor's hearing is impaired so we suspect he was abandoned at a shelter because he was not able to "do his job" on a farm. Thor is up for an adventure, whether it's hiking on a nature trail or strolling along Detroit's River Walk.
Fence Requirements: Large fenced in yard.

DOG APPLICATION: https://service.sheltermanager.com/asmservice?account=dr1937&method=online_form_html&formid=26

CAT APPLICATION: https://service.sheltermanager.com/asmservice?account=dr1937&method=online_form_html&formid=41

EXOTICS APPLICATION: https://service.sheltermanager.com/asmservice?account=dr1937&method=online_form_html&formid=46

The information we are providing for this animal was developed based on observations and assessments in a shelter or foster environment. We do our best to provide information that will help determine if the animal might be a good fit for you. Please note that behaviors may change in a home environment. We also ask our applicants to assume that any animal they adopt from us will need to be potty-trained and learn house manners, although this is not always the case. In most cases, the listed breeds are also a best guess. Our online animal bios are designed to provide as much information as possible and answer some anticipated questions. We do not have the resources to respond to emails with more specific questions.

We are receiving an unusually high number of applications at this time! Applications are reviewed as they are received, but we do not select adopters on a first-come basis. Our job is to ensure each pet is placed into the best fit home for them and that adopters are paired with an animal that is a good fit for their lifestyle. All animals will stay online until they are "pending adoption". Therefore, if an animal is still listed, we are still accepting applications for him/her! Please do not send inquiries about a specific animal's availability as this can change quickly over the course of the day. The fastest way to get a response is to simply submit an application! We will do our best to notify you by email if the pet(s) you are interested in are no longer available. New animals are posted daily, so please let us know if another furry friend peaks your interest (there is no need to fill out a second application)!

Fill out the application (DOG:https://service.sheltermanager.com/asmservice?account=dr1937&method=online_form_html&formid=44, CAT: https://service.sheltermanager.com/asmservice?account=dr1937&method=online_form_html&formid=41, EXOTICS: https://service.sheltermanager.com/asmservice?account=dr1937&method=online_form_html&formid=46) completely. Every question must be answered, and it must be signed.

-Applicants must be 21+ years old and live within a 50-mile radius of our shelter at 22415 Groesbeck Hwy, Warren 48089.

-You must identify at least 1 animal that you are interested in.

Once your application is received, it will be assigned to one of our volunteer Adoption Counselors who will follow-up with the applicant who is the best fit within a few days, or to discuss other options. It could take up to a couple of weeks for you to receive a final disposition on your application so there is no need to check on the status.

-Introductions will be scheduled by appointment only, 30 minutes per appointment. The entire household, including current dogs, must be present for the appointment. (Note: Please do not bring your dogs if you are meeting cats!). The introductions will take place outside in our parking lot (or in our cat room if you're meeting cats).

-We will perform vet checks for current and prior pets in the household.

-Finalizing the adoption will also be scheduled by appointment.

Thank you for your understanding.

name: Kiara
description: Nala and Kiara are the female kittens from the Lion King Pride litter. These two little girls are very curious...
full_description:
Nala and Kiara are the female kittens from the Lion King Pride litter. These two little girls are very curious of what is going on around them. They are the definition of mischievous! They love to climb as high as they can to observe their surroundings or to just take a nap, so a cat tree is a must! They are 10 months old and are doing great at using their litter box and they are eating well.
Nala is the quite observer who can be quite the silly girl at times. She loves to be out with everyone looking for mischief. Nala plays well with her littermates and does well with other cats also! Kiara likes to play hard with other kittens but she also likes to chill and observe with her sister, Nala. They are both great because they are a wonderful mixture of chill and play.
Nala and Kiara both have an adoption fee of 75 each or 100 if adopted together. They are vaccinated, FIV and FELV tested negative, microchipped and spayed.
Many kittens do better with another cat in the house, for this reason you can adopt one or both of these wonderful 10 month old kittens. You can apply for either one, or both Nala and Kiara at www.pawpatroldayton.com/adopt. All of our animals are vaccinated, micro-chipped and spayed/neutered before being adopted.

name: Miss Peanut
description: Miss Peanut is a charming, funny and brave senior dog. She is an affectionate dog who loves to cuddle up...
full_description: Miss Peanut is a charming, funny and brave senior dog. She is an affectionate dog who loves to cuddle up with her human friends. Miss Peanut loves a good adventure and is very curious. She is friendly to humans and can be acclimated to dogs. Peanut also does well with cats. She would do best in a quiet home where she can get lots of love and attention. She is a senior dog but has teenager energy in between naps. Her perfect home is one with a nice yard, and someone who can spend a lot of time with her, and who can give her the love and patience she needs and deserves. She is an adorable dog and very funny, and will make you laugh every day. If you're looking for a sweet, loyal, and funny companion, come meet Miss Peanut!

name: Marley
description:
Meet Marley – A Sweet Husky in Need of a Loving Home 

Marley’s story is one of heartbreak and resilience....
full_description:
Meet Marley – A Sweet Husky in Need of a Loving Home

Marley’s story is one of heartbreak and resilience. This beautiful, pure white Husky was abandoned by her family when they moved to Tennessee, leaving her at the Cleveland pound on their way out of town. Facing the risk of euthanasia due to overcrowding, Marley was rescued just in time. Now, she’s looking for a forever home where she will never be left behind again.

2 year old female spayed husky
UTD with Vaccinations
Dog- and cat-friendly
Affectionate & Loving
Crate trained – but she’d much rather snuggle in bed with you!
Good on a leash

She currently weighs only 36 lbs and needs some TLC to reach a healthier weight.

Marley is an incredibly sweet, gentle soul who deserves a second chance at a loving home. If you’re looking for a loyal companion who will adore you unconditionally, Marley is your girl!

Would you consider opening your heart and home to her? If you’re interested in fostering to adopt, please apply https://3husketeersrescue.com/adoption-applications
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
PA Law (3 P.S. Section 459-207(f.1))
3 Husketeers Rescue Spring City, PA
PA Kennel License #17204

name: Lil Coop
description:
Meet Lil Coop, named in honor of Super Bowl champion Cooper DeJean. Here’s his story.

"We live on a dead...
full_description:
Meet Lil Coop, named in honor of Super Bowl champion Cooper DeJean. Here’s his story.

"We live on a dead end road. People are constantly dumping trash. We have had several cats get dumped. When we had the freezing temps, we heard an unusual animal-like cry in the wooded area of our property. It was the puppy. We took him in and got him warm and have cared for him since. I called the county and they said they were not taking any animals because of they were overcrowded. They directed me to the SPCA of East Texas." ~~ The Person Who Saved Him

10 weeks old Shepherd/Akita Mix
Crate Trained
UTD with Vaccinations
Neutered
Microchipped
